animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

animal.description:
**Milan is expecting! We are accpeting applications for adoption, but she won't be available to go to her forever home until puppies are born and weaned early 2021. She will also be spayed after puppies are weaned.**

Milan is an 11 month old female husky mix that was rescued from an abusive situation in Missouri. She is great with dogs, cats and chickens. She is also an expectant momma. The Italy Litter is coming soon!

The suggested adoption donation for Milan is $400. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
Meg is a beautiful 3 year old, 40 lb Staffy Blend looking for a home.  She was rescued from a high kill shelter in Texas.  She is currently in foster in Colorado waiting for a new family.  She is truly a sweet dog that loves to climb in your lap and snuggle.  She is truly a lover dog and needs that kind of love returned.  She would be a perfect dog for a couple or single person that doesn’t have any other pets.  She would also be best in a home without small children, sometimes she doesn't know how big she is.  She doesn’t do well with other dogs which is the main reason her current foster can not keep her.  Her foster loves her to death and knows she will be amazing for a single person or couple with no children.  She is hoping to find her family for the holidays.  She would make a great hiking buddy or even a long walking buddy.  If you would like to meet sweet Meg please fill out an application at

www.lowridersofthewest.org

Meg’s adoption fee is $375.00 - she is spayed, up to date on all her vaccinations and chipped.

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is TREVOR.  What’s yours?  Nice to meet ya!  

WATCH MY VIDEO:  https://youtube.com/shorts/NLcPVEpmMCM

https://youtu.be/1tXnnodjV3s

If you like me, ask my foster for a better video!

A nice person came along and took me in and, now, I am ready to hit the road to your house!  Uh, make that “our” house, OK?  I definitely need a house with a fenced-in yard cuz I need room to run and romp and be safe!  The rescue requires (1) a fenced-in yard and (2) a vet reference from a vet that you have used for a current or previous dog to be sure that all vetting was done.  

I am a Whippet/Terrier mix.  I am 8 MONTHS old and I weigh 25 pounds.  I will probably weight 35 - 40 pounds fully grown. I have been neutered and am up to date on vaccines so I'm ready to go to my new home with YOU!!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I am fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  They say I'm precious.  Hmmm, Is my name Trevor or Precious?

Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like ALL people and ALL dogs.  I need to have a DOGGIE SIBLING so we can run and romp together and burn up LOTS and LOTS of energy!   If you don't have a doggie sibling, I need someone who can play with me and love on me a w-h-o-l-e lot!  How about all day and evening, every day?  OK?

I have lots to learn.  Will you teach me all the things a pup needs to know to be safe and happy? I LOVE to give kisses so get ready!  

If you have children, then need to be older children - 12 and up because I like to play hard and run fast!  It's fun!

Since I was rescued, I've learned to use a doggie door at my foster's home.  Smart, huh? I like to take naps when I'm tired from playing.  I need  love, exercise and couch-sitting when we get tired!  Let's be a team, OK?

If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email rescuedogsgalore@gmail.com  and they can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  Once you adopt me, I will be flown to Seattle from Houston, TX.  (That's the only place we can fly to right now.)  My adoption fee is $450 and includes my vetting, neutering, flight cost, travel crate, Health Certificate and a microchip.

animal.description:
Berlyn is a gorgeous 2 year old, 60 lb. Lab mix. We are looking for a special home with patience and hopefully room for her daughter who is not a Labs4Rescue dog. Berlyn is house trained, has perfect house manners, and is great with other dogs, cats, and kids. Berlyn is very sweet and affectionate and has medium energy, she's playful, but not hyper. She was rescued from a hoarding situation and when we got her, she was afraid of everything. She has come a long way, but is still nervous with new people and new places so her adopter will need to be very patient and understanding to help her be comfortable. Berlyn has some separation anxiety and she would love a home where she isn't left alone for long periods. Berlyn's new home should have a physically fenced yard and she should never be walked off leash.

For additional information about Berlyn please email Marla Cox at mclabs4rescue@gmail.com. 

Berlyn is being fostered in New England.

IMPORTANT INFORMATION: We receive many questions about our adoption process from potential adopters, most of which can be answered by viewing our "Adopt a Lab" page on our full service website, https://labs4rescue.com/.   To expedite the process, please follow the step-by-step instructions outlined and submit an adoption application listing 3-5 dogs of interest. Please hurry as your new best friend is waiting for you!

ADOPTION FEES: $445 non-refundable adoption fee for all vet expenses (spay/neuter, shots, etc.) and transportation to ensure your lab gets to you in a safe, professional manner. All fees may be paid using PayPal, cashier's checks, or money orders. Labs4rescue does not accept personal checks for adoption fees. All adopters must pay their Labs4rescue adoption fee prior to the rescue shipping their dog.

Residents of Massachusetts or New Hampshire are required to pay an additional $125 fee, which defrays the cost of their state's mandatory 48 hour isolation and examination by a licensed veterinarian.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Looking for a an active, amazing, easy-go-lucky boy? Major is your guy! Major is right at 2 years old and came from the streets of Texas. Like so many of our dogs, he has had to fend for himself for a long time, yet you would never know it from his personality.

Major loves kids, shows no interest in cats, and plays well with the 6 other dogs at his foster's house. He thinks running, chasing balls, and playing with the people is the best day ever. Major is a high energy dog and would do best in a household where there is plenty of opportunity to play, hike, run, and just have an all-around good time. Don't forget to leave room from him to snuggle with you on the couch at the end of the day!

With his intelligence, Major will be a fun dog to train. He has little to no training and will highly benefit from some good training sessions. He is learning potty training. (When a dog lives on the streets, there is no such thing as the "right" place to go!) He does walk nicely on a leash and thinks car rides are amazing. His foster is currently working with him on a little food aggression issue that is a throwback to his street days. Again, this will all come with training.

Are you looking for an active boy that you can bond with over some great training sessions? How about someone that is happy to see you anytime and loves having the people to play with? Major is a win on both fronts. Major is currently fostered in Winchester VA and looking to talk with you!If you are an approved adopter and are interested in this dog, please let your case worker know. If you are not yet an approved adopter but are interested, please complete an adoption application!
You can review our adoption process, www.shenandoahrescue.org/adoption-process if interested. Donations can be made at shenandoahrescue.org/donate or on PayPal to info@shenandoahrescue.org

animal.description: This sweet boy is Bubba. He was found near southern junction on 276 in Rockwall on 12/11/20 and never reclaimed. He is a male, 6 year old Chocolate lab/Bloodhound mix who weighs a whapping 97 Lbs.! Bubba is a big boy! He is also a love bug and is very social with people. He does well with kids and would love a family that will play with him. He also loves to go on walks but can be more of a puller when on a regular collar. So a harness is definitely recommended. Bubba appears to be crate/house trained and knows some basic commands too. He does not do well with other dogs and is not suggested with cats. He just likes to be the center of attention. Bubba is not one that can be left alone in a back yard alone as he has proven to be a little bit of an escape artist. He can very easily escape a chain link fence so he will need a home with a wooden fenced in back yard or something like it. He just gets very scared that he will be abandoned when he is left alone in a backyard for extended periods of time. Once he gets good and settled in a home and builds trust his anxiety should subside. Other than that and his dislike for other animals, Bubba is a really good boy and just needs a family to love. His adoption fee is $125 which includes my neuter, rabies, microchip, basic boosters, and heartworm test. Bubba is heartworm negative! If you are interested in meeting Bubba, please complete an application online today at https://rockwalladoptions.com/adoptfoster/adoption-application/All animals unless otherwise noted in their descriptions are at 1825 Airport Road, Rockwall, TX. Hours of operation are Monday through Friday 9 AM - 6 PM and Saturday 9 AM - 5 PM. For questions, please call 972-771-7750, ext. 2 or e-mail info@rockwalladoptions.com.All animals, unless otherwise noted in their description, are at 1825 Airport Rd. in Rockwall, TX. animal.description:
Introducing Helga-don't worry, she will not be upset when/if you decide to change her name :) She is a 30 pound, 9 month old pitbull mix. She has the cutest facial expressions and super fun ears. She loves to go for car rides, even though it sometimes upsets her tummy. She gets super excited to go trail running with her foster mom and enjoys walks around the neighborhood. She loves to do zoomies in the backyard.

Helga is fostered with kittens, puppies and adult dogs. Helga attaches herself to her people very quickly. She loves to spend lots of time with them! Because of her love for her people, she has some jealousy issues when it comes to sharing them with other dogs. In order to overcome these jealousy issues and perfect her sharing skills, she needs an owner that will set firm boundaries. With additional training for both her manners and sharing skills, she can learn to share her people with other dogs in the home.  Helga is overly interested in the cats in her foster home and would likely do best in a home without cats.

When Helga came into rescue, we learned she is nervous of new people. She needs time to adjust before they’re best friends! She should not be rushed into new situations so she can acclimate and adjust accordingly.  Once she is comfortable around you, Helga's entire body will wiggle when she greets you. She is eager to please her person and is intelligent, often learning commands very quickly. Helga has such a fun personality when she gets to know you and trust you.  If Helga sounds like the dog for you, apply today!  Her adoption fee is $250.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
UPDATE: Crystal is trying her best to adjust to the hectic shelter life, and she sure hopes she can find her forever home soon. We have discovered that the one thing Crystal loves is having us sit with her and pet her. She is truly a dog that thrives on affection and being with a special person. She becomes so calm, ignores all the noise and just gazes up at you with complete adoration while you are with her. We wish people could see this side of Crystal, she just needs a calm gentle person and a calm quiet home where she can be the only pet. 
Crystal is an energetic girl who loves to play fetch and go for long walks in areas that are not busy with a lot of other dogs. She knows the command for sit and likes to play with toys, and her favorite activity is being with the one she loves. Crystal is looking for an experienced home with people who will understand that she needs a steady routine, lots of love and affection, and a secure 6 ft. fenced in yard so she can play, get her energy out, and relax safely when she goes outside. Crystal will be the love of your life and if she gets the right home she will be the best dog.
**If you are interested in adopting Crystal, please contact the shelter at 509-662-9577 to schedule an appointment to meet her!

animal.description: Little Imani is the sweetest thing ever. We cant even imagine the hell she went through just trying to survive. The pictures dont even do justice to showing how emaciated she really is. Despite the nightmare Imani was living, she still LOVES people. She has a wonder disposition and takes treats very gently. Imani is only about 1-2 years old. She will need some work with housebreaking but she seems very smart and we expect her to catch on quickly. Imani does well with calm dogs with proper introductions, but she does resource guard with other animals. She initially tested ok with cats, but has since shown very questionable behavior with them. At this time we would recommend a home with no cats. Imani is very energetic and still very puppy like, so training classes are a requirement with Imanis adoption. Imani is now healthy and is scheduled to be spayed. We are now accepting adoption applications for her. We posted Imanis original link below if youd like to read her complete story. animal.description:
We show our dogs by appointment only upon receipt of our online application which can be found at kcpaws.petfinder.com If you are reading this, we are still accepting applications for Abuelo. The adoption fee for Abuelo will be $150.
Abuelo is a handsome, sweet 10 year old Chihuahua. He's the happiest guy around and loves to snuggle and wants to sleep with his owner. He gets a long fine with other dogs and prefers to hang out with them when not snuggling with his person. He is one of 5 senior Chihuahuas who were given up to a shelter when the owner moved so he's used to living in a pack of dogs. That doesn't mean he wouldn't love to be a spoiled only dog too though.
Abuelo has had some trauma to his pelvis in the past, likely hit by car and his bones did not heal correctly. He has luxating patellas as well on both back legs so this gives him an very unusual gate. He gets around just fine though and loves to do his business in the yard then run as fast as he can back to his foster mom to be picked up and carried back inside. He is on a daily anti-inflammatory pill to keep him comfortable and will likely need that for the rest of his life.
He's very sweet and just wants a home of his own to live out his golden years. If you are interested in Abuelo, please complete our online application.

If you are looking for a best friend and constant companion, 7 year old Ella is your girl!!  Ella needs time and reassurance to feel comfortable in a new environment, but once she has time to learn and acclimate to a new household dynamic, she is a total snuggle bug who wants nothing more than to be an integral part of the family. Ella is cat friendly, seems to like other dogs who are respectful, and would do best in an adult only home or a home with children over 12 who are able to give her space until she's ready to accept their love. Ella did not know any commands when she came to Kodi’s Club but has learned sit and is working on learning down in her foster home. Ella likes long walks, long cuddles, games of fetch with a large ball, belly rubs, boofing at the mailman, and food!!  To make Ella's transition from her foster home to her adoptive home, we will ask approved applicants to visit with her prior to taking her home.  If you think your home might be a good fit for Ella, you must complete the application on www.kodisclub.org.

**If you are serious about adopting , you must head to our website at www.kodisclub.org and submit a completed application . DAKOTA came to us a few weeks ago from a shelter where he was an owner surrender. Initially he was very scared and nippy but we discovered much of this was due to his pain from dental issues and his eyesight which is compromised due to cataracts.  He had a much needed dental  and is now very much happier! He likes to go on walks and ride in the car too!  His ideal home would be as an only dog ( he does tolerate the other dog in his foster home though)

DAKOTA is 12yrs old and weighs 12lbs.  He is not fond of being groomed, although he came to us in poor condition so his coat had to be shaved down.  He is now a much happier boy and will come to you to be pet and for belly rubs.  He needs an understanding family to go slowly with him until he learns to trust again. 
Pomeranians are one of the longest living small dog breeds ,often living until 20yrs old!

If you would like to adopt this special  senior boy please go to our website www.somersetcottagepoodlerescue.org and click on adopt to download an adoption application 

DAKOTA'S adoption donation is $595 to help cover his large vetting expenses.

animal.description: Scout #6941 is a handsome 3-year-old Lab mix. He is calm and sweet. His foster describes him as extremely well-mannered. Scout loves to lay on the couch and be lazy with his people. He is both crate and house trained. He is very strong on leash when he has to go potty, but once he has taken care of business he is more relaxed. We are working on leash etiquette. Scout knows the commands sit, stay, shake and walk. He is very attentive to commands and knows how to take treats gently. His favorite activities are watching the world go by out the window and sleeping. Out on walks, he loves to sniff everything. Scout loves to sit by the feet of his favorite person (especially with his tongue hanging out). He loves big comfy beds. He loves treats and food. He is good at meeting other dogs, but is food aggressive so if there is another dog in the home they MUST be fed separately; may be best as an only dog or with strict feeding rules. Scout does best with older children who understand boundaries, as he does not like people in his face. Scout rarely barks at all and is a very quiet young man. His favorite game is tug-of-war with a rope toy. Stuffed toys and Scout do not mix well - he will tear them up within minutes and make a big mess! His favorite time of day is the morning, so that he can greet you! He weighs 85 pounds and is full grown. This pup is microchipped. We believe you can always teach an ‘old’ dog new tricks, so we highly recommend continued obedience training for this smart pup; it stimulates the dog's mind and establishes a good dog/adopter relationship. This pup, like all pups, should be on heartworm preventative; an ounce of prevention is worth a pound of cure. If you are interested in adopting this dog, and are already approved to adopt through our organization, please contact dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with the pup’s name and ID number in the subject line. OTHERWISE, please submit an adoption application online: http://www.lastchanceanimalrescue.org/adoptus.html E-mail dogs@lastchanceanimalrescue.org with questions. Stay tuned to our Facebook page for updates: www.facebook.com/LCARMD #adoptlove #PicMe #petsmartcharities

animal.description:
There are moments in rescue that you come across a dog that has experienced unfathomable cruelty.  Your heart breaks at the thought of what all she has experienced in her lifetime.  But she is a survivor - a sweet,  but shy girl who only wants to know love.  And love is what we shall find for her!

This beautiful survivor is Miley - a 7 year old Collie/Terrier mix who weighs 43.6 pounds.  She experienced extreme violence and trauma in her past life when a cruel human attacked her with a machete - causing the scar above her eye.  

Despite this cruelty, Miley is a sweet girl who seeks love and attention from those she trusts.  She is shy, but loving and will require gentle guidance and patience in her new home.  We do believe that she will do best in a quieter home, with kids over the age of 13 years.  

After spending a few days in a foster home, her foster family was able to share some new information with us about Miley.  They have found that Miley is more comfortable outdoors than in, especially while she's learning to trust.  Once she is familiar with her surroundings, she seems more inclined to stay close to her person, however she is a flight risk.  Miley requires a secure fenced yard and supervision during yard time.  As one can imagine, she can be pretty nervous about new situations and she will look to her person for encouragement.  She does enjoy walks, but a proper harness will be needed for the moments when she might be inclined to back away from a situation.  Miley takes great joy in chasing birds and squirrels - even if that means chasing them up a tree.  With this prey drive, small animals might not be a good fit. 

Her minimum adoption fee is $275 plus a $12 fee, if 4 months or older, for rabies registration for McLean County residents. She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm 

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

animal.description:
Angel is an 8 (ish) year old, spayed female, 95 pound, Mastiff/Bully type dog. 

She came into our care in December 2019 when was was abandoned and hit on the highway. Thanks to all of our friends and the awesome doctors and staff at the vet, Angel was made healthy again.

We all love our girl, and we know there is an ideal forever home out there for her.

Things that we know of Angel, are that she needs leash training. Her adopter will need to be dedicated to working with a trainer to make her the ideal walking partner and to get her  entree socialized around other animals. Currently she is not friendly around other animals.

Angel LOVES to go for rides and hang out with her people. She loves people and  should be fine with older children, but due to size and unknown history, we are not comfortable placing her with young children in the home.

A securely fenced yard where she can run and play safely, would be most ideal.

For more information, please call 860-428-4422

animal.description:
If you have ANY QUESTIONS or are truly interested in adopting any animal from PAW Animal Shelter Please, fillout an adoption application FIRST! WE are a high intake No Kill Shelter ran by a staff of 4 and do not always have time to answer every question asked by so many. If you are a good fit for the animal you are interested in -we will call to speak with you, If we feel you are not a good fit , we will contact you about other pets that may be a good fit for your home. Many people are losing the opportunity to adopt the animal they want because they fail to put in an application and the pet was adopted before we could answer your email. .If you have applied for an animal in our facility and have not received a response within 7 days, PLEASE call or contact us again. Though we do our best in trying to answer all emails in a timely manner, sometimes things get away from us, get lost or misplaced. It is never our intention to ignore a request about an adoptable animal in our facility.

Sandy Brown, Director, PAW Animal Shelter

319-372-2274

animal.description:
Meet Arthur! It seems like this silly boy is always smiling! He is a 2 year old Lab/Retriever mix who is medium sized at about 45 lbs. Arthur's foster family reports that he is a wonderful, polite houseguest with good manners and a sweet disposition. He enjoys exploring outside and playing with toys, especially stuffed animals, but is most happy when he is getting lots of pets! Arthur gets along fine with other dogs, but would do best in a home without cats. He does love to be the center of human attention, so Arthur would really enjoy easygoing doggie siblings who don't mind if he hogs the spotlight. With that big goofy grin, how can he not steal the show? Contact ARF to meet Arthur today!

-----
IMPORTANT: To protect the health of our staff and volunteers, ARF is currently conducting adoptions by appointment only. Please see more information below.

-Contact Info: Have questions first about the adoption process or a particular animal? Please contact us at inquiries@animalrescuemobile.org.

-Ready to Adopt? Please visit www.animalrescuemobile.org to submit an adoption application.

-The Adoption Process:
An adoption application, veterinarian and/or personal reference, a home visit, and a $150 adoption fee are part of the process. All animals will be up to date on shots, microchipped, and spayed/neutered before adoption.

-Please Note:
Sponsors are needed to help ARF with the cost of vet care. If you would like to sponsor an ARF rescue, please click the Sponsor Me button. A sponsor donation of $50 will help cover the cost of a spay/neuter surgery. Plus, ARF is a non-profit organization and all donations are tax deductible.

animal.description:
Meet Pearl! Our best guess is that this cute girl is a shepherd mix, approximately 8-10 months old and 40 pounds.

Pearl is extremely sweet and loving with her humans. She absolutely loves to run and chase squirrels, so she would love a yard to play in, but she enjoys taking walks as well and with someone who could give her a minimum of two long walks each day she would be fine! Pearl is happy to spend the day playing with her toys and napping while her human works the day away!

Pearl is looking for an experienced owner who can work on training. For this reason, she would be best suited in a household without children or other pets.

Interested in adding Pearl to your family? Apply online today!

If you are interested in adding this pup to your family, please submit an application at www.petrescuealliance.com. All questions will be answered and meet and greets set up following a review of application. If the dog is listed on our website or Petfinder, they are still available! Pet Rescue Alliance does our best to provide accurate information about the dogs we have available for adoption. We cannot make any guarantees about age, breed or temperament.

animal.description: Ollie IS AVAILALBE (updated 02-02-2021).To meet any of our dogs you must first complete our online adoption application on our website. For more information and the adoption application for Ollie, please visit our website belowhttp://www.coastalgsr.org/dog_profile.php?ID=22281&name=OllieOllie is a big and handsome White GSD whom we rescued from the shelter. He was originally picked up as a stray and adopted through the shelter, but, two years later, his adopter was moving and didnt consider Ollie in his plans, returning him to the same shelter from which he was adopted. When his time there ran short, we offered him a life vest and welcomed him into the Coastal family.This gorgeous boy didnt appear to have been socialized much with people, had horrible fly strikes on his ears, and is timid about life, in general, leading us to believe that he lived those two years in a yard and saw little else beyond the fence. Weve been working with him for a few months now and see that he needs help in trusting strangers and becoming more confident, so he will need a low traffic home with someone who believes in him and can show him life is fun and not scary! Around 3-4 years old, Ollie is a gem with the volunteers he knows and trusts, has honed his leash skills so much that he's now considered easy to walk, and is looking for someone to show him structure and give him leadership so that he can feel confident and comfortable in his new life. The minimum adoption donation for adults is $375 and the adoption donation for puppies is $500. This amount only partially covers the cost of veterinary care, boarding fees, and other miscellaneous expenses involved in the temporary care and adoption of our dogs and is tax deductible. The adoption donation provides that all dogs will be spayed or neutered, receive current vaccinations, and are microchipped. If not, arrangements will be made on an individual basis ( i.e., puppies who will need to be altered by 6 mos old). Special consideration may be given to those willing to adopt older dogs or dogs with physical problems.

animal.description:
Name: Beans
Suspected Breed(s): Pit Bull Mix
Gender: Male
Age: 1 year
Weight: 96 lbs
Personality: Gentle giant, happy, friendly, playful, goofy, quiet, calm, easygoing
Observations with Dogs: Good with other dogs
Observations with Cats: Untested
Observations with Kids: Gently takes treats from the 1 year old and 3 year old children in his foster home. Beans loves to give them kisses, and occasionally inadvertently knocks over the 1 year old because Beans is not fully aware of his size. 
House Training Progress: No recent accidents
Crate Training Progress: Does well in crate
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Smyth County, VA
Additional Information: Beans was found as a stray with his collar embedded into his neck. It has been removed and he has healed well. He is a friendly, gentle giant who is not only beautiful but is amazingly calm. Even when other dogs are barking at him and going nuts Beans just stays by his persons side and looks at the other dogs. The menacing household Roomba is a different story Beans does his best to protect the household from this marauding vacuum by barking at it. Beans has done well with the young children in his foster home, and doesnt try to chase them, even when they squeal and run away from his abundant kisses. Long walks are a favored pastime for Beans, who will thrive with an adopter who enjoys walking 2.5 - 3 miles a day. Beans is a smartie who knows the word sit, and he is looking forward to learning more tricks in his forever home.

__________________________________

If you are interested in meeting a dog or cat, we require an adoption application. If the animal has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon. Apply for a DOG: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adoptable-dogs.html

Interested in saving more lives? Foster a dog today! Learn more, see our list of dogs needing foster, and apply, https://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster-a-city-dog.html

City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is a foster based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR&CK has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs and cats (we do not operate under a first-come, first served model).

Upon accepting a new cat or dog into the organization, we provide a basic vet visit that includes necessary vaccinations, disease screenings, deworming, microchips, and spay/neuter (unless specified). We do not provide a comprehensive medical exam prior to adoption. As a result, sickness, injury, and disability may exist unbeknownst to CDR&CK. City Dogs Rescue & City Kitties is not responsible for payment of any vet care, including known and unknown medical conditions once a cat or dog is adopted from us. 
Dog specific: Rabies, DHPP, Bordatella vaccines. They are tested for HW, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasmosis.

Most cats and dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any pet is housebroken or crate trained.

We also update our Facebook page daily with new cats and dogs.

animal.description:
Meet Sadie!  Sadie comes to us from the shelter where she came in as a stray, and was tagged with  behavioral issues.  After carefully getting her home and getting her checked at the vet, we found that this poor girl was suffering from a VERY painful pancreatitis and enlarged liver and an ulcer in her eye.  Plus, her teeth were an infected mess.  Her pancreatitis is resolved and she has had her dental work completed. Her ulcer is gone but she will need eye drops for dry eye for the rest of her life. 

Sadie is a sweet girl, and hasn't shown any behavior issues since being home with her foster.  She timidly comes toward you and loves to have you rub her nose and back, and even shows you a little tummy now and again.  She loves walks, naps in her fluffy bed, and loves playing with her Westie sister.  She had come out of her shell, and is a real sweetheart.

animal.description:
Hi, I’m Cathy! I’m a 3 year old hound / terrier mix and am full grown at about 35 pounds. I’m a goofy love bug with a zest for life - I love being a part of the family, shiny stuff, my food, treats and belly scratches! My foster family thinks I'm one of the sweetest dogs there ever was and is super excited for whoever decides to bring me into their life furever.
I'm great with big hoomans (even ones I've never met) and little hoomans too (I lived with some of 'em, they were great!) I have excellent indoor manners and while I won't chew your things or break into your food, I'm always ready to cuddle up next to you on the couch and love going into my crate for a good night's sleep.
I'm still getting used to being on the leash (but am doing better with my front harness) and would reallllllly appreciate getting to live with a hooman that can help me learn to contain my excitement when I see other dogs (though I love playing with them when I'm off leash!) I've never lived with a cat but don't chase them when I'm out (squirrels = different story!) 
I can climb a fence, so I require supervision outside (I am a doggo!) I don’t need to stay outside though, because I’m perfectly potty trained! I’m also spayed, up to date on my shots, and currently finishing treatment for my heartworm. 
Do you have a place for me in your home and your heart?


*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2020 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

animal.description:
Approx 1 yr old.
Approximately 13-15 pounds, and is black in color.
Very good with and LOVES to play with other dogs.
Follows his foster mom around the house.
JUST WANTS TO BE LOVED!!
Very friendly.
Bobby came to us from Mexico.  He had been hit twice by cars and left on the side of the road for dead, for several days. Once someone realized he wasn't dead yet, a kind Samaritan took him to an animal hospital. She contacted rescues for financial assistance, and Bobby was given treatment for his injuries.  He walks on 4 legs with a little gimp, runs on 3 legs,  and is cross-eyed because he was untreated for so long.  NOW, he's pain-free, happy, and as healthy as can be.
Bobby is neutered and has his microchip.  He has all of his shots also.  
Bobby would like a home with someone that is retired or works from home permanently.  He would LOVE another dog, similarly aged, to play and live with. His adoption fee is $375. 
If you are interested in meeting or possibly adopting Bobby the Lovebug, please email us at AdorableDogRescue@yahoo.com telling us a little bit about yourself, your home and yard, and the time that you will be able to commit to Bobby.
Bobby will go quickly because he is healthy (in spite of his leg and his eyes), and is very loving.  Bobby is so grateful for the help he received, and lives joyfully with the other dogs!! He needs to be picked up and petted, and loved on to become fully socialized. 
Please email us as soon as possible with the info requested. We'll take down the profile as soon as he is adopted. Thank you!!

animal.description: Abandoned and unwanted. Found by a good samaritan at an empty house. What we do know he was kept outdoors since he was adopted from a local shelter. This we know because of the thousands of sun spots on his undercarriage.  He is super sweet his original name was Yeller. We contacted the original owners and they surrendered him verbally to us. He was examined by our trusted vet and diagnosed positive for Heartworms. The rescue started the expensive treatment with little funds and did not raise much for his care. We finished the treatment in November and still have an outstanding balance at the vet. He has been kept on heartworm prevention and he is happy and jolly boy. The last part of the treatment for him was a bit rough but he's a survivor. Now with a happy heart we can find this boy a well deserving home to keep him happy and healthy. He is very smart and appreciates the care and love given to him by me so it will be bitter sweet to see him go. My goal is to place him in the best home/environment/lifestyle/family possible. If interested to do a virtual meet and greet first. Contact Jessie by email : jessie@1luckydogrescue.com or text 786-486-4188. Thank you.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.ATDR 3296Meet Mojo. He and his best friend Rambo have been together since they were tiny puppiestheir precious mom loved them more than anything. So sadly, this young woman became very ill and slipped into a coma with no hope of recovery and recently passed away. We're not sure how long she had been hospitalized and unable to care for the boys. There were no family members who could take Mojo and Rambo so they were surrendered to ATDR. We couldn't say no to these orphaned babies who have been sad and confused to the point of not eating well and losing some weight since their mom had to leave them. They're now in a loving foster home where they'll be cared for and nourished, physically and mentally, until they feel safe and hopefully secure again. Circumstances like Mojo and Rambo have experienced are very hard on pups who have never known anything but the love of an owner they totally adored.
These precious babies are bonded and for now having each other is the most security they feel. Rambo is fairly dependent on Mojo who comforts and sweetly watches over himboth pups are very sweet, friendly, playful, and well socialized. They came into rescue with a crate, a doggy bed, supplies and a garbage bag full of toysit's so obvious how much they were loved. ATDR is currently bringing their vetting up to date and then they'll be ready to go.
12.19.20 Their foster mom reports: Mojo and Rambo want to wish everyone a very Merry Christmas! As seen by these precious little sweaters, their sweet mom apparently liked to dress them as twins...
These boys are good dogs. They go straight into their bed (crate) for a treat or whenever I open the laundry closet where the treats are kept. I feel comfortable leaving them free roaming in the kitchen when I'm working upstairs or when I go work out.
The boys are getting more playful and starting to show their true personalities. Mojo is a real card (does anybody use that saying anymore?). He loves to disembowel stuffed toys and tear apart indestructible toys, i.e. Kongs. The consensus is that Mojo looks like an Ewok from Star Wars but he could pass for a Wookie too, and since that is easier to say so I refer to him as 'The Wookie.' Mojo enjoys being loved on but he's a busy, independent boy, not needy, clingy or demanding of attention. When it comes to TV time, he prefers to lie on the other end of the same couch or even on the other couch. He doesn't lie by me (at least not yet). Rambo, on the other hand, likes to lay by me and get under the blanket. He's sweet and cuddly. He's not obsessed with destroying toys like his brother. Mojo is definitely the dominant of the two. He sometimes punks Rambo out of toys, food, etc. Rambo seems more dependent upon Mojo for a sense of security, but they are definitely bonded to each other. They lie in the same bed together frequently. If I separate them, e.g. for a bath, the one left behind will fuss. They're very precious cute boys!
Mojo and Rambo need to be adopted together. Won't you please consider giving both these boys another loving homehelping them become the secure happy pups they were before losing the person they were totally devoted to? If you would like to make their lives complete again, please fill out an adoption application. In no time at all they would love you more than you could ever imagine

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.ATDR 3300Meet Rambo. He and his best friend Mojo have been together since they were tiny puppiestheir precious mom loved them more than anything. So sadly, this young woman became very ill and slipped into a coma with no hope of recovery and recently passed away. We're not sure how long she had been hospitalized and unable to care for the boys. There were no family members who could take Rambo and Mojo so they were surrendered to ATDR. We couldn't say no to these orphaned babies who have been sad and confused to the point of not eating well and losing some weight since their mom had to leave them. They're now in a loving foster home where they'll be cared for and nourished, physically and mentally, until they feel safe and hopefully secure again. Circumstances like Rambo and Mojo have experienced are very hard on pups who have never known anything but the love of an owner they totally adored.
These precious babies are completely bonded and for now having each other is the most security they feel. Rambo is fairly dependent on Mojo who comforts and sweetly watches over himboth pups are very sweet, friendly, playful, and well socialized. They came into rescue with a crate, a doggy bed, supplies and a garbage bag full of toysit's so obvious how much they were loved. ATDR is currently bringing their vetting up to date and then they'll be ready to go.
12.19.20 Their foster mom reports: Mojo and Rambo want to wish everyone a very Merry Christmas! As seen by these precious little sweaters, their sweet mom apparently liked to dress them as twins...
These boys are good dogs. They go straight into their bed (crate) for a treat or whenever I open the laundry closet where the treats are kept. I feel comfortable leaving them free roaming in the kitchen when I'm working upstairs or when I go work out.
The boys are getting more playful and starting to show their true personalities. Mojo is a real card (does anybody use that saying anymore?). He loves to disembowel stuffed toys and tear apart indestructible toys, i.e. Kongs. The consensus is that Mojo looks like an Ewok from Star Wars but he could pass for a Wookie too, and since that is easier to say so I refer to him as 'The Wookie.' Mojo enjoys being loved on but he's a busy, independent boy, not needy, clingy or demanding of attention. When it comes to TV time, he prefers to lie on the other end of the same couch or even on the other couch. He doesn't lie by me (at least not yet). Rambo, on the other hand, likes to lay by me and get under the blanket. He's sweet and cuddly. He's not obsessed with destroying toys like his brother. Mojo is definitely the dominant of the two. He sometimes punks Rambo out of toys, food, etc. Rambo seems more dependent upon Mojo for a sense of security, but they are definitely bonded to each other. They lie in the same bed together frequently. If I separate them, e.g. for a bath, the one left behind will fuss. They're very precious cute boys!
Rambo and Mojo need to be adopted together. Won't you please consider giving both these boys another loving homehelping them become the secure happy pups they were before losing the person they were totally devoted to? If you would like to make their lives complete again, please fill out an adoption application. In no time at all they would love you more than you could ever imagine

animal.description:
Snowbell was originally part of a hoarding situation in the Tulsa area. The lady turned many dogs over to local rescues, but was allowed to keep 4 dogs. Snowbell and Crackers were two of the dogs that she kept. Unfortunatly a year later she passed away. The dogs then found themselves at Tulsa Animal Welfare. A foster family took the chihuahuas in to get them out of the shelter. They then came here to ARF. Snowbell is still nervous, but is a sweet dog. Her and Crackers are bonded and we would love for them to be adopted together.

Fill out an application at the link below. Find the dog/cat you are interested in and click the adopt button. That will take you to an application. Once approved you will be called for an appointment to meet your possible new family member, or at that time you can meet the other animals as well. https://petstablished.com/public/search/shelter/301551

Adoption fee is $150 which includes, spay/neuter, vaccines, etc, and a free 1 year membership to our 5 acre ARF Park. For other dog questions please email ARFdogs74006@gmail.com

We do adopt out of state, but the adopter must travel to ARF to meet the dog they are looking to adopt. They must have an approved application before traveling to meet the dog. We do allow small dogs that are eligible to fly in the cabin of a plane. We DO NOT allow dogs to travel in the cargo area of the plane under any circumstances. Any dog that is adopted can of course go by personal vehicle. We do not allow dogs to be transported "pony express style" where they are passed from driver to driver.

animal.description:
Please note: Secure visible fencing is required to adopt Jesse.

Jesse is a sweet and affectionate big fella (110 lbs)  that will love to can lay at your feet and get petted all day. He also loves being brushed. Jesse loves to go for car rides and walks and has nice leash manners.

Jesse is kennel trained and took no time at all to learn that his kennel is a good place where he eats and sleeps. He knows the word "kennel" and willingly goes in when asked to do so. Prior to rescue Jesse often went without food and shelter. For these reasons, he can get anxious about food. Jesse needs to eat in his kennel and hang out there when his people leave the house. He gets fed twice per day in his kennel and his favorite snack is a peanut butter dog cookie!
 
Jesse is completely housetrained and has never had an accident in the house. He knows to go to the door when he needs to go outside. Jesse loves to run around the yard to play and watch the neighborhood and park adjacent to our property. However, we discovered that he does not like the wild turkeys that come by or the excited neighbor dogs who run around off leash. So a 6ft fence is best for this big guy.
 
He gets along great with our cat and our other Pyr who is very calm. Jesse feels nervous around high-energy or anxious dogs. He will do best in a home with another calm dog or as an only dog. He does well with our 13 and 17 year old kids but the 4 year old neighbor boy makes him nervous so a home with older, calmer kids will be best. 
 
Jesse is believed to be about 6 years old. He is neutered and up to date on all shots and heart worm negative.  Because of severe matting, 6 pounds of mats were shaved off Jesse before he came to NorthStar.
 
Jesse is not a trained stock guardian and will be placed as an indoor family pet only. An adoption application, secure visible fencing, a site visit, and an adoption fee are required to adopt Jesse.

animal.description:
Oreo is a male chi estimated to be about 2 years old. He weighs 8lbs and, as you can see, is colored just like an Oreo cookie! 

Oreo has a long story, and if you stick around long enough to hear it, you'll realize he's really worth it. Oreo is not a social, outgoing dog and never likely will be, but he's sweet and deserves a lot of love! Oreo came from an irresponsible backyard breeder where he lived outdoors and had no socialization. 

He came into rescue with a bad skin infection, and would defecate from fright if anyone came near. We had our work cut out for us, and as far as he has come, he still has a ways to go. He will get there one day, with the right family to love him. 

Oreo has been in foster care for a year and a half. Foster mom and dad successfully weaned him from the corner he lived/hid in, and watched as he gradually integrated himself into the household. Small, tiny baby steps the entire way, 

Oreo now freely roams the downstairs, timidly goes upstairs- but only for brief periods of time, and is trying his best to walk out the front door on his own to leash walk with the other dogs in the pack, but still isn't quite there yet as he finds the unfenced world a scary place. 

He freely goes outside in the fenced backyard, and will jump up on the couch to take a nap. His favorite place is a dog bed, the blanket on the couch, or in the backyard in the sunshine. He is a creature of habit and does not like change. 

Moving to a new place will provide a whole new set of challenges for him, but with patience and dedication, he will succeed. We've lived with the same routine for a long time and he's done well with it. 

He is very food motivated, but also very stubborn. He is still learning to accept gentle touches and would do really well with someone who has time to dedicate to work with him. Each night he jumps up to snuggle with Foster mom, and as simple as that sounds, that's a really big deal! 

He is now crate trained and sleeps nightly in his crate.  He gets up in the morning and wags his tail and is really excited for his day! As for potty training, he teeters on the threshold of knowing he needs to go outside to go potty, but has a spot inside (where he used to live) that he tends to go (Foster mom leaves a pee pad there) and pees on it regularly. 

He is a flight risk- a large one. He's very frightful of loud sounds, new people, and needs a very, very patient family. It's taken him a long time to do normal dog behaviors that most people take for granted, in fact foster mom has only just now been able to pick him up and hold him without him trying to flee. Simple things are very large for Oreo. 

Oreo doesn't like new people and would not be a good fit for small children. Oreo has taken pride in his foster home and feels he needs to protect it, he barks at all visitors and sometimes nips their ankles even! 

Foster mom and Dad feel he's come far enough to move to a dedicated home who is looking to successfully help him integrate and live a life of luxury. 

Oreo would do best in a home with small dogs. He loves to play, and he does really well following the pack. He would likely not do well as a single dog in a new place. The only car rides Oreo goes on is to the Vet. He is frightened but seems to do better each visit. 

Oreo will come to you when called, if treats are involved, or he knows it's meal time. Otherwise, he generally needs a lot of coaxing and would need someone to understand it will take him a while to understand a new routine. 

Every milestone he reaches is a cause for celebration. He has more to meet, and his new home should understand the time it will take for him to trust, and that he will not make new people best friends easily. 

He is neutered, UTD on shots, HW neg and on HW prevention.

His adoption donation is $250.00.

If you are interested in the above dog, please do not email us and tell us that you are interested, but submit an adoption application. The link for the application is below.

To submit an application go here……chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application/
An application must be submitted and approved before a meet-n-greet can be scheduled.

Your current dogs/cats must be spayed or neutered unless a veterinarian has determined that your current pet(s) should not be fixed due to medical reasons. 

They must also be up-to-date on shots and on HW preventative.Reference checks and a home visit are required so SE dogs can only be adopted in NC/SC, VA, TN, AL, MD and GA.

Tru Blue weighs 47 pounds and his date of birth is 10/11/2018.

You can submit an adoption application for this handsome boy at http://www.fayettefcar.com/applicationform, where you can also review FCAR’s adoption requirements.

All FCAR adoptable dogs have been spayed or neutered, are current on all vaccines, on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, microchipped, and come with a 30-day pet health guarantee. The adoption fee is $95 with an approved application. A fenced yard is required for Tru Blue.

animal.description:
Kharma and Lucky, the inseparable duo! 

Kharma and Lucky were owner surrendered to Springfield Animal Control after the families landlord said they could no longer have them at their residence. They were kept separated during their stay at Animal Control which left them heart broken, Not understanding why they were all alone. Left behind by the only family they had known, not even able to take comfort in each other as they've always done. When someone from Animal control reached out to C.A.R.E. we knew we had to do something to give them hope.  

We gladly welcomed both Kharma and Lucky into the C.A.R.E. Family. It was such a happy moment to witness them being reunited upon their arrival, At that moment we made them a promise.. We promised to find them a loving and devoted home where they could stay together forever!  

Lucky is a 9 year old white male American Pitbull terrier mix. Kharma is a 5 year old brindle female American Pitbull Terrier mix. Losing their lifelong family was very hard for them but a brighter future awaits them! They are currently at the C.A.R.E. Sanctuary enjoying some much needed TLC while awaiting the perfect family to welcome them into their lives and home. Khamra and Lucky would love to have a privacy fenced yard to run and play with their new forever family!

animal.description:
If you see a dog listed on Petfinder, then that dog is currently available in our rescue. You don't need to email asking if they are available. 
The crucial first step is to fill out an application @www.camorescue.com

Buddy is a 1-2 year old, 10 lb. chihuahua looking for some warmth and cuddles. A little playtime with some buddies around his size wouldn't hurt either. Once bonded  with his human He is right there by their side. Buddy will follow you around or pop himself onto your lap, he will sleep by your side and burrow under the covers.  And when you come home from work he is so excited to see you that he will wrap his legs around you.  Buddy is potty trained and crate trained! 

ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/camorescue

Our donation link is http://www.paypalme/camorescue 

We are strictly volunteer based, no salaries are paid and 100% of donations go towards rescuing dogs.

animal.description:
Shelby is a gray and white 3 year old pittie mix that weighs in around 70 lbs. She has the most beautiful eyeliner and a wiggly body just made for snuggling.

Shelby comes off a bit shy when you first meet her, but once she opens up, let the kisses and pets begin! She loves snuggling with her humans and is happy to just chill by your side all day long. She is a great home office dog, and is pretty low energy. Even on days when weather doesn’t permit a long or good walk, she is content to just curl up and nap with you or at your feet. She LOVES to give kisses.

Shelby has a lot of dog school under her belt that makes her a well-behaved pup. She does, however, prefer to be the only dog in the home. Shelby was adopted into a family through PFP and was recently returned to our rescue after the family realized she did not get along with their resident dog, even after training and time. She does enjoy going on pack walks and occasionally running the fence with neighbor dogs, but she would be a best fit in a home as the only resident dog. She also needs a cat-free home and a home with older kids or adults only. 

Shelby is crate trained and very trustworthy. Her foster family has never had to worry about her destroying things or climbing on furniture. She currently lives alongside a live Christmas tree and barely touches it or looks at it. Her tail on the other hand… that’s her most powerful weapon! Silver lining is, that’s how she shows her happiness – with her tail and her whole body. So you know she’s always a happy girl!

If you’d like to meet Shelby, please visit www.playersforpits.com/adoption-survey today!

animal.description:
Dixie Belle is a beautiful English Springer Spaniel mix, about 10 years old and 37 lbs. She’s a gentle, sweet & loving dog that loves all the cuddles she can get! Her favorite spot is on your lap where she can completely relax with you. She has a big appetite and sleeps easily through the night. This lil' lady loves being around people and is very quiet and laid back. Dixie Belle is housetrained, walks well on the leash, and is well past her puppy stage.  She is great with other dogs and cats and is a very easy going girl.  This poor angel was rescued out of a pond and had a very difficult life before coming into our care.  She will light up your world instantly!

Dixie Belle is blind and deaf but gets around pretty well.  She does have elbow dysplasia and arthritis, so she is in need of an adult home and extra care such as guiding her outside and picking her up on staircases.  This special girl deserves only the best, so we are looking for a special home for her to spend the rest of her life being spoiled like the princess she is.  


Thank you so much for your interest in adopting a dog from A New Chance Animal Rescue (https://anewchancear.org). We are a 501c3, tax deductible organization. ANCAR is a foster-based rescue, and we adopt within a 90 mile radius of Bedford Hills, NY.  You will find the adoption application here: (https://anewchancear.org/adopt/adoption-application/).  All fields on the application must be completed.
Please read about the adoption process (https://anewchancear.org/adopt/adoption-process/) so you'll know what to expect when you submit.   

Our dogs are in foster care and we do NOT have a shelter or boarding facility. AN APPLICATION MUST BE COMPLETED IN FULL AND APPROVED BEFORE A DOG CAN BE MET. This is a firm policy. Our busy volunteers are not able to respond to questions about the dog or dog meeting requests in the absence of an application.  We know these dogs very well because they are in foster care. Please read the profiles of the dog(s) you are interested in prior to submitting an application.  If there are specific requirements stated (ie: Fenced Yard or Canine Friend Required) these are included because they are vital to the happiness, health, safety and adoption success of that dog. 

We are only able to save as many dogs as we have foster homes (https://anewchancear.org/foster/faqs/) and resources for. We provide medical care including vaccinations, testing, deworming, spaying/neutering and microchipping before transporting our dogs. We provide all supplies, preventatives and any follow up vet care necessary while they are in foster care. These costs are high and the number of lives we can save is entirely dependent upon donations from people like you.  We do not receive funding from private foundations or government sources. If you can find room in your heart to help us, with any amount, we are truly grateful (https://anewchancear.org/help/donate/). We are a 501c3 organization, so all donations are tax-deductible. It is only through the kindness of supporters like you that we are 'changing lives...one tail at a time' by providing our dogs with 'A New Chance.' (https://anewchancear.org) 

Thanks so much.
animal.name: Dixie Belle

animal.description:
This pretty little momma is Destinie.  She is just over a year old and came to us with a liter of newborn puppies in tow.  Momma and babies are doing very well.  She is still pretty protective over her puppies but other than that is doing great. 

We were told she is a Lab Mix but we believe she may have some Terrier in her because she does have some sections of her coat that look Terrier.  She isn't very big at about 35 lbs.

We were told that prior to having puppies she was good with other dogs - since she is still nursing we haven't yet attempted her with another dog here at the shelter.

She certainly appears to be housebroken.

She should be ready for her very own home the first week of January 2021.  Her adoption fee will be $250.00.  She will be spayed, current on shots, wormed, heartworm negative and micro-chipped.

An application to adopt is mandatory and must be tentatively approved to even visit the shelter.  To fill that out go to OUR website at www.patriotsforpets.com and you will find the application under the Adoption tab..

animal.description:
Meet Incubus, an eleven-month-old American Pit Bull Terrier mix.

Incubus is a handsome boy who loves people, he gets super excited when he meets people and is all over them in his excitement, because of this it might be best he goes to a home with no young children who might accidentally get knocked over. He has never met a stranger in his life and loves treats "sitting" for them. Incubus also enjoys playing with squeaky toys and just being a big goober, he currently weighs 50 pounds. When he really wants a treat he will talk to you with big, low woofs that will melt your heart. Incubus has met the YHS house cat.  He is very excitable around cats and will chase them, and due to his behavior he cannot be in a home with cats.
Update* Sadly Incubus was returned again due to his higher energy level.  He will do best in a home that is active and has a large fenced in yard.  Incubus is still very puppy and tends to be mouthy and jump up on people.  He will need an experienced adopter that is comfortable training a large dog.
Update* Incubus was adopted but had to be returned due to him jumping up on the adopter's senior mother. He is a very active and happy boy who needs a similarly active adopter who wants to help him with his training. 

If you are interested in adopting this pet please fill out an adoption questionnaire at www.yakimahumane.org. A Yakima Humane Society staff member will contact you once your questionnaire has been received.

If you would like to adopt this pet you can fill out an online adoption form at www.yakimahumane.org. Please give the name and ID number for the animal you wish to adopt.
If you are thinking about adding a pet to your family, be a hero, please consider adopting a shelter pet and if you already have pets – for life’s sake – spay and neuter. Spaying and neutering your pets is the single most important thing you can do to help decrease our nations severe pet overpopulation.
*NOTE: Nearly 90% of the animals that come into our shelter are abandoned, neglected, traumatized, injured, or ill. We attempt to give our best assessment of the animal’s welfare and temperament. Unfortunately, due to lack of funding, volunteers, and resources our physical and mental assessment of the animal is not always 100% correct.

animal.description:
This big love is about 70 lbs and 2-3 years old! Cabezon is Staffie / Pit Bull mix, H/W negative, fixed, and received all his adult shots including rabies on 8/17/20. 

His backstory is that he was wandering on our street one Sunday, hung out with us all day and then took off. My husband spotted him on his way home the next day with a homeless man. It was clear he had been attacked by another dog and was in need of some vet attention. The homeless man told Miguel he could no longer care for him and asked that he take him. The dog was seen by our family vet that day and again later that week. We later named him Cabezon, big head and hard head in Spanish :) We thought we had some potential adoptions lined up on our own but we are now happy to have Pup Squad help us find a good, responsible home for him. 

He's a great dog that loves hanging out with other dogs and people, but not cats. He's a large, strong dog and needs an owner that can handle a dog his size with a yard for him to run around and play because he loves toys and tug-of-war. Being an ex-street dog, in the beginning he would try to leave and jumped our short 4 foot fence with ease. He doesn't anymore but a tall fence is definitely a requirement for any potential adopter. He is crate trained, does well on a leash, and we're still working on other basic commands. He's super friendly and just really sweet natured despite his tough appearance!

Our adoption fee is a $250.00 donation to Pup Squad Animal Rescue. Our adopted dogs are all spayed/neutered, vaccinated and micro-chipped. If you are interested in adoption, please go to www.pupsquad.org/adopt to read more about our policies and find our application. Applications should be submitted via the online form http://pupsquad.org/adopt/adoption-application.html. 

During COVID 19 - We may not be able to help coordinate transport out of state due to limited resources on our end and limited transport options to get the dogs to destinations outside of Texas.

Thank you for choosing to rescue an animal in need!
www.pupsquad.org

animal.description:
Ynonna arrived at Horse Creek Wildlife Sanctuary on August 14, 2020.  

She is a gentle and loving lady!  She is laid back and seems to enjoy every moment of her life.  Ynonna enjoys playing outside with other dogs and loves receiving affection from people.

She weighs 55 pounds full-grown, and we believe she is a German Shepherd mix. 

Ynonna would make a great fit into a loving and caring family! Wouldn’t you like to have this sweet girl in your life?

All of our dogs are spayed or neutered and are current on all vaccinations. They are on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention. All of their medical needs are taken care of before they are available for adoption. Our adoption fee is only $100.00. Please complete an application, if you have found a dog you are interested in adopting. You can find our application at www.horsecreekwildlife.org/applic.html. Once completed, you can forward it to adoptions@horsecreekwildlife.org or fax it to 731-926-3000. Kim Austin, our adoption facilitator, will be in contact with you as soon as she has an opportunity to review your application. Understand that she has other duties and she will not ignore any interest shown in adopting one of our dogs. An application will need to be approved before a scheduled time to visit our dogs will be set up.  It may take up to 48 hours before she returns your call or responds to your email, due to work schedules, holidays and adoption events. We do the very best we can for the dogs we have rescued and do not take the adoption process lightly. Please be patient and understand that we will place our rescued dogs in the very best homes possible and reserve the right to refuse applications.

animal.description:
Caesar is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Caesar is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~7 years
Weight: ~79lbs
Housebroken: Yes
Crate trained: Working on it! Takes some time to settle (10-30 minutes) but has done well both in a crate and when sectioned to a confined area (bedroom). 
Dog sociability: Friendly with dogs on walks! He's a big boy and pull towards dogs to say 'hi!!' as he is very playful. Will benefit from a confident handler.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Unknown, but he can be mouthy (play bites) when overly excited so best suited for older kids/teenagers
Ideal home: Caesar is looking for an active adopter that can continue to work on training! He is not a match for a high-rise/elevator building but is adaptable to most other living environments! 

Pizza! Pizza! There's nothing Little about this Caesar! This gentle giant will have you wrapped around his paws as soon as you see those giant puppy-dog eyes and adorable ears. A very sweet and loyal dog, Caesar is the best! He is a playful and active pup, so don't let his age fool you! His online dating profile would read that he loves long walks, is an avid runner, and enjoys nothing else more than to rest his big ol' head on your lap during snuggles. Caesar is doing well with his training and has great basic commands. This is an incredibly sweet pup who even put up with being squeezed into a holiday sweater that just barely fit over that adorably large noggin! He also loves to carry his stuffed toys on walks which might be the cutest thing we'eve ever laid eyes on. After one play sesh, this Caesar is guaranteed to Veni, Vidi, Vici your heart!

Due to a generous donation, Caesar's adoption fee is now sponsored. He is neutered, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm negative. He will require booster vaccines at the adopter's expense. 

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
Meet Hennie! 

This petite pittie is 8 years old and weighs approximately 32 lbs. She is a little underweight currently and will be up to 40-45 lbs when healthy! Hennie is housebroken and crate trained. She is also spayed, up to date on vaccines, and will be fully vetted before adoption! 

From what we know/understand about Hennie’s past she has not lived an easy life. She has had multiple litters of puppies, likely has lived as on outdoor dog, and hasn’t been given the love and attention she deserves. That ended for her thanks to her amazing foster mama! Hennie deserves the spoiled life of a loved companion and to live life as an indoor dog. Hennie is on the shy side and takes some time to warm up to knew people, but we know with the perfect home she will flourish and show her amazing personality. Her new family will need to understand it may take a little bit for her to warm up. Hennie is beginning to hangout on the dog beds, chew bones, following her foster mom around and attempting to play with her furry foster siblings. She would thrive with another social/playful dog in the home. 

To adopt Hennie fill out our adoption application online at the link below
www.bullluvablepaws.org/adopt

animal.description:
Noel is the perfect work from home companion who is very happy to hang out at your feet all day. She won't bother you for more than a little attention and a walk, and she may snore audibly during your afternoon zoom call, but it is very cute. She is crate trained and very comfortable hanging out in there, but she doesn't need the crate, just a safe place to mellow out for the first few days that she's with new people. 

She is very friendly with most dogs, and is happy to play with her foster brother for a little while. She recently had puppies, and is getting back to her ideal shape, so after enough training with her foster brother she will be ready for hiking season this summer. Noel is a little more hesitant in warming up to people, and warms to females a little quicker. Once she knows you, she will be happy getting as much attention from you as you will give her. She is house trained, walks great on a leash, and is working on new skills. 

*Homeownership Required! Subject to BSL.

	Spay/Neuter

	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella

animal.description:
Talk about a unique boy! Donovan will be the talk of the town with his adorable nose speckles! This super friendly guy showed up at our shelter as a stray. He has been charming our volunteers and staff ever since! Donovan is full of energy and always ready for any kind of shelter activities. He loves to go for walks and zoom around our play yard in his free time. Donovan would thrive with an active adopter that is looking for a new sidekick. Donovan was friendly with other dogs when introduced, but would likely need a slow introduction to other dogs in the home. He ignored cats, but will need monitored with them to be sure he isn't going to turn into a kitty chaser. We think Donovan would do best in a home with older children due to his size and energy level. Donovan is waiting to meet you, get your application in today!

If you're interested in meeting or adopting Donovan, please complete an application at: inapl.org/adoption-application. Once it's processed, a member of our team will be in touch with you to schedule a meet and greet appointment. This is the time when you and all members of your household will come to our shelter to officially make your connection with Donovan.

animal.description: Oreo is super fun, sweet and lovable. She is only 10 months old. Like all young pups, she is active and playful and will keep you on your toes. Oreo loves to go on adventure outings with our staff and volunteers. Hiking, long walks in the park, taking rides in the car, hanging out with human friends and playing are her favorite things to do. Oreo knows some basic obedience skills and is already house trained. She is working on her patience and manners. She can get over-exuberant when she wants to play so she will need your help with structure so she doesn't get over excited! Reward-based training is best. She is eager to learn and treat motivated. Oreo loves enrichment and chew toys and to play, play, play. If you are looking for an outgoing, social, love bug who will keep you motivated to exercise then head over to our Eastside Shelter to adopt Oreo. Weight: 62 lbs Housetrained: yes Dogs: meet and greet, would need management and a well matched doggy companion Cats: unknown, never been around Children: recommend kids over 12 due to strength, over-exuberance and mouthy-ness when playing
