animal.description:
****Please read Noelia's ENTIRE BIO before emailing or submitting an adoption application!**** 

*Name: Noelia
*Age: 3-4 years old
*Current Weight: 25 lbs
*Location: Currently being fostered in Carmel, NY
*Adoption fee: $300

**Noelia's foster mom's posts lots of videos of Noelia and her foster siblings on TikTok (@dogmom76)! Check them out! **

Noelia was found on the border of Texas and Mexico in September 2019 in a cemetery where she had been dumped with her 4 nursing babies :( When she was first rescued, Noelia had a spinal injury that left her paralyzed in her hind end. She had no use of her hind legs. Sadly, she was not producing milk and her babies did not make it. SNARR put her on transport to NY and one week later she had surgery by a top orthopedic surgeon to fix her spine. Within a week of her surgery, she was standing with assistance and by week 2, she started hydro and physical therapy. By week 5, this amazingly resilient girl was RUNNING! 

Noelia is a sweet, gentle soul. She didn't know how to be a dog when she was first rescued. Beds, toys and treats were like wonders to her. She used to ask permission to take a toy, but now she just goes for it. Watching her blossom has been incredible! It does take her a minute to warm up to new people and surroundings, but once she knows she's safe she is a happy, loving little girl! She will come to you for affection and loves her head scratched. She is learning how to play and is quite the goof when she is in the mood! She loves toys, and loves to be outside exploring more than anything else. She likes other dogs, especially those who will play with her. She's not shy about food at all! At mealtime, she bolts to her specific spot in the kitchen, sits and wait her turn. No one taught her this -- she just watched what the other dogs did and is a quick study! She is super smart, gentle, and would be great with a patient family who understands she is a bit shy and needs help to bring her out of her shell.

Noelia's ideal home: Noelia will need a family who knows she is still becoming the dog she was meant to be; one that will continue to keep her active to maintain the physical progress she's made, and also who will help her continue to heal emotionally from her past life on the streets. No small children, please. We feel they are too wild for her comfort. She will never bite or snap, ever, but we know she'd do best in a calmer environment. Noelia must have a home with another friendly, female, confident pup and a fenced in yard. She is a remarkable girl with a remarkable story of recovery. 

To apply to adopt Noelia, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

*Health: up to date on required vaccines, spayed, microchipped. Noelia was hind-end paralyzed when she was first rescued in 2019, but spinal surgery helped her regain feeling in her hind legs and she is completely mobile now! However she does need her bladder expressed daily as a result of her original spinal injury. Her foster mom will happily show any adopter how to do this, as it's pretty simple!

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING

**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

If this listing is still posted, we are still accepting applications for him/her. We do not do out-of-state adoptions on highly adoptable dogs; we would only consider out-of-state adoptions for dogs that prove hard-to-place locally. We cannot hold dogs, please submit your application when you are ready to adopt. PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING PARAGRAPHS FOR INFORMATION ON THIS DOG, AS WELL AS INFORMATION ON OUR PROCESS.

Gobi is around 10-11 months old and weighs 36 pounds. He is estimated to gain no more than 5 pounds to be at his full-grown weight. He was rescued with his mom, Olivia (also available for adoption) and sister Mojave (who has since been adopted). He is sociable with other dogs and loves to meet new canine companions. He is shy at first and requires some confidence building. Once he adjusts, he is a very loving companion. He will embrace affection and become the happy puppy we know him to be -- he just needs some time and patience to get there. He would be good with calmer, mature kids over the age of 10 years old. His adoption fee is $385 which covers the cost of his neuter, all core vaccines (Rabies and Distemper/Parvo), microchip and microchip registration. The first step is completing an application which is available on our website, poochmatch.com, under the adoption tab. Please read the below paragraphs for more information on our process.

UPDATE: ADOPTION EVENTS CANCELLED DUE TO PANDEMIC AND SOCIAL DISTANCING. If you are interested in meeting any Poochmatch dog at our weekly adoption event on Saturdays at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda, CA (5521 Mirage St.) between 1-5 PM, please fill out an application from our website, poochmatch.com, and submit it no later than 11 AM on Fridays. Upon receipt AND approval, the dog you are interested in meeting will be made available to meet on a Saturday. Due to the high volume of dogs and puppies in our foster homes, it is impossible to bring them all every Saturday. The only way to ensure that the dog that you are interested in will be at the adoption event is to FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AND BE APPROVED. Otherwise, we cannot guarantee that the dog you are interested in will be at our adoption event. If you cannot make the time frame of our events, appointments can be made at another time and location solely at the discretion of the foster parent. Please understand that private appointments will be coordinated to meet the convenience of the foster parent/transporter.

All adoption fees cover the mandatory and non-negotiable spay/neuter, rabies, microchip, microchip registration, full sets of core vaccinations (rabies and 1 set of distemper/parvo for adults, 4 for puppies) and deworming. Adoption fees vary based on age, breed, size and the costs incurred on the dog's behalf by us i.e. medical, behavioral training, etc. and they range from $225-$495.


COVID-19 PROCEDURE:
In an effort to create a safe environment for our potential adopters and our staff, we have changed our protocols and procedures during these difficult times. Starting immediately, our procedures will change from what’s written on our website and other social media platforms. Our weekly adoption event at the Petsmart in Yorba Linda is temporarily cancelled due to COVID-19 and social distancing. The only way to meet one of the dogs/puppies we have available for adoption is through completion of our adoption application through our website, poochmatch.com, before 11 AM on Fridays. On Fridays when we review the applications, we will pick the best fit for each dog or puppy applied for and coordinate mutually agreeable appointment times for the applicants who are approved that week. Private appointments are currently only scheduled on Wednesday, Thursday or Saturday of each week. Masks or bandanas are mandatory; faces must be properly covered.

With the overwhelming desire of the public to adopt at this time, we have received as many as 30 applications for one dog in just one week. Working with a staff of volunteers, we are only able to reach out on Fridays to the people we have approved to adopt. If you have not heard from us by Friday, we have selected a different applicant. If you have multiple dogs/puppies that you are interested in, please indicate each dog/puppy of interest on the application at that time so we don’t rule you out for another dog/puppy available for adoption.

Please understand, we have an influx of texts, phone calls and emails that makes it impossible to get to each and every one of you. Not just for adoption interest, but also from veterinarians, people who must relinquish dogs, people who have found a stray dog in need of pick up, etc. We are currently not in need of fosters. Due to the fact that there is such a high demand, we are sticking with strict protocol to not adopt out of Southern California. We apologize for this inconvenience and difficulty to be able to get in touch with us while there is an overwhelming desire and demand to adopt at this time. We appreciate your understanding and patience as we navigate through these difficult times with every intention to keep the public and our staff safe.

Frida 
5 years old
47lbs 
Hw+

Frida came into the rescue as a pregnant mom brought in off the streets. Due to an infection as well as malnourishing living conditions, mama Frida lost all 8 babies within 12 hrs of coming to us. 

She has now healed and is full of energy and life. She is great with children 8 and older, as well as other dogs who respect her personal space. Because she has street smarts, she doesn't like to share her food, toys, or bed. She would thrive in a home where her boundaries can be respected.

Frida is spayed, up to date on shots and microchipped. She is also crate trained, working on leash training, and she has shown no aggression towards children. animal.description:
Asher, Opal and Raven are shy Labrador mixes looking for a special angel to give them the home they have never known.  Most of their previous life was spent outside without much human interaction.  Now that they have come into our care, all have blossomed.  Asher is almost two years old and the mother of nine month old daughters, Opal and Raven.  All are medium sized dogs that weigh less than thirty pounds.  This is a bonded tight-knit family that loves each other very much.  Asher, Opal and Raven do best when they are together.  Consequently, we are hoping to adopt them to the same family.  These pups are looking for a simple life with a family that enjoys life in the slow lane.  They need a calm quiet household without a lot of people coming and going.  An adult home or one with older children would be best.  These girls are really very sweet but quite timid and reserved.  They are perfectly content to go about their day as you do whatever it is you need to do.  Most of the time, you will find them curled up together for a nap or taking turns with a chew toy.  They are quiet, well behaved, and housebroken if kept on a schedule.  None are really into walks, but they will follow you out nicely to their own fenced in backyard.  They love running around together and spending some time outside exploring.  Over time, we introduced other calm well-balanced dogs to their play group and all have responded well.  Another confident stable dog may be a benefit in their new home to help them adjust.  Don’t expect this bunch to run up to greet you when you walk in the door.  They are just not into hugs and kisses.  A good meal, a warm bed, and a soft gentle voice to tell them they are loved are all they require.  They really are quite easy to please.  If you have room in your family for three dogs, please consider Asher, Opal and Raven.  It would really warm our hearts to see them in a forever home of their own.  

To adopt this pet, Click "More About Us" and then "Adoption Application" to be directed to our online HSNWGA application form.  You will be contacted by our Adoption Coordinator once your application is reviewed and approved.  Due to high volume of applications, we are only able to contact those applicants that best meet the needs of that individual pet.

MEET MS. ROSIE BEING FOSTERED IN JACKSONVILLE, NC! 

Rosie is a six year-old pit bull terrier that is looking for a family to call her own. Rosie has not had any issues with cats or other dogs in her foster home and is house trained, loves children and just needs a wonderful loving home.

Rosie weighs approximately 50 pounds and her main caretaker is her favorite eight year old in the home! She absolutely adores children. She does pull on the leash a bit but a bit of training can get her moving in the right direction on that! 

If you want a loving pup to hang out with you on the sofa or in your recliner .... Rosie is your girl! She would truly prefer to be the only dog but does live with other dogs in her foster home. It would be best for Rosie to live with a low key dog. 

Rosie came in heartworm positive and she is being treated with the slow kill method. She is doing great and has recently lost the extra weight she had coming into her foster home.

animal.description:
To be considered for adopting a dog from Canine Lifeline, you must have an approved application must be on file. Please visit http://www.caninelifeline.org/adoption-process/ for more information about our adoption process and to submit an online application.

Titus is a very handsome 5 year-old Black Lab who was surrendered by his family along with Sadie, a 3 year-old Chocolate Lab, when they could no longer care for them. In their previous home, Titus and Sadie lived outdoors and slept in a doghouse. Fortunately for them, those days are over and they will be living in comfy indoor homes from now on. True to his breed, Titus is a very friendly and outgoing dog who loves to play with his human friends but doesn't usually realize how big he is. At 90+ pounds, when this boy starts jumping for joy, it's a sight to behold. Titus does sit nicely for a treat so should be able to learn lots more in his new home as he's very food-motivated. Since coming to Canine Lifeline, he has done extremely well with crate-training and keeps his crate spotless. With continued crate-training and some consistent positive direction on the part of his new family, he should have the housetraining routine in his new home mastered without too much trouble. Titus has not had a lot of experience on a leash yet so would benefit from using an Easy Walk Harness as he works on his leash skills. He's a very eager to please guy who needs lots of exercise and some direction from his new family. Titus lived with kids in his previous home and did well with them although given his size and exuberance, he knocked them over on a regular basis. Titus has gotten along well with all other dogs he's met since coming to us. Although he lived with Sadie previously, Titus and Sadie do not need to be adopted together although they would make a great pair for the Lab lover looking for two active dogs. Titus weighs about 90 pounds and his adoption fee is $350. He's neutered, heartworm negative and on monthly preventative, up to date on vaccinations including bivalent canine influenza, wormed, on flea and tick preventative, and microchipped. As part of the adoption process, all adopters must commit to a two-week adjustment period to make sure it's a great match before the adoption is finalized. Please email info@caninelifeline.org if you're interested in Titus. An approved application is required before we schedule meets with any of our dogs. Please note that we don't place our dogs in homes with children under 7 years of age. We correspond via email so please check your junkmail or spam folder to make sure our reply hasn't landed in there. animal.description:
Hi my name is Misty and I am a  pretty female Terrier mix who weighs 37 lbs. and I am 7 years young. I came to the rescue with Buster who was adopted and living his happily ever after life after our owner died. I also was adopted but I turned out to have too much energy for them so here I am back looking for my furever home. I am a sweet girl who loves my humans and will stick to them like glue but I am high energy terrier and I do have a motivation to hunt as you see I lived outdoors my whole life! I like to follow my nose and investigate new things and can be a digger too. I have never lived in a house so it is all new to me, so I will need to be crated when you are not around to watch me. I am very smart and learn quickly but I will  need some kind person or family (older kids would be best) will teach me how to be a pet. I have not had much human interaction in my life, so my social skills are not that great. I do LOVE people and I am very playful. I am now crate trained but still need to understand house manners which I am working on. I need to be an only dog, no cats and in a home where I will get lots of exercise and play time! If someone would work with me and give me a chance, I know I have the potential to be the best dog ever! Praying for my home for the holidays. If you would like to make me yours, please fill out an application on the rescue's website www.floprva.org that is the only way to be considered to adopt from this nice rescue who gave me a chance to find you! 

Love, 
Misty xo

animal.description:
Meet little Phoebe, a very sweet and loving, 12-lb, 4-year-old Chihuahua mix who is dreaming of the best Christmas present ever... a loving forever home!

Phoebe loves people, and also loves giving  kisses. We feel she will do best in a home as an only dog.

Phebe is well housetrained, but doesn't want to be in a crate. She loves sleeping quietly under the covers with her foster mom, and hopefully her new family will welcome another addition the 'the big bed'. She rides well in the car and enjoys walks on leash. Even though she is young, Phoebe enjoys being a 'couch potato' or hanging out on a warm lap.

Phoebe is deaf, and some people consider it a handicap. There are many positives to having a deaf dog! First, she doesn't bark every time the doorbell rings. Then there are loud noises such as thunder, fireworks, and gunshots... no problem for Phoebe. When all the other dogs are barking, Phoebe does not even chime in! She'll sometimes 'talk' to you, but that's when she is wanting something. 

Because Phoebe is deaf, she must have a fenced yard to insure her safety. A family with someone home most of the day will be best so she can go 'potty' on a regular schedule. Phoebe seems to love children, so a family with gentle children, or grandchildren should be fine for this sweet girl.

Phoebe is spayed, micro-chipped, and current on her Rabies and DHP/Parvo vaccines. She tested negative for Heartworms and intestinal parasites, and is currently on Heartworm prevention.

Phoebe's adoption fee is $300.00

Forever Home Canine Rescue offers a 3-week trial period with all our adoptions, just to be sure that the pet is a good match for the adoptive family. The fee is refunded if the adoption does not work out within the trial period. We want to be sure that each of our pets will have their perfect 'forever' home!

If you are interested in Phoebe and think she may be your ideal canine companion, please visit our website at foreverhomek9rescue.org for information on our adoption process. To get an application, you can cut and paste this link to our online application: http://foreverhomek9rescue.org/adoption-application. You may also download an application from our website, or e-mail us at foreverhomeK9rescue@yahoo.com for additional information or to request an application.

Forever Home Canine Rescue adopts out-of-state, but we never 'ship' or 'transport' our pets. An approved adopter must come to North Carolina to meet their new canine companion and then take him/her back home with them.

animal.description: It's heartbreaking and enraging to think about the awful life Mya endured.  She showed up in early 2020 at someone's house in miserable condition - emaciated, covered in mange and fleas and ticks.  That nice person took her to the Vet and she got Heartworm tested (miraculously negative), vaccinated, and started on a number of medications for her fleas/ticks, mange, skin and ear infections. When she came here we continued and added medications.  When she was strong enough, she was spayed and had a mammary tumor removed.  Then I noticed that her face looked like it was melting and realized that her upper mandible was broken and not attached to the roof of her mouth.  I feared this poor long suffering angel had cancer and would never get a chance to know love and comfort and joy.  But the Vet did surgery and believes it was trauma. GRRRRRRRRRRR. She has had two surgeries to close the hole in the roof of her mouth, and even though it is still open a bit, she does GREAT eating and even LOVES LOVES LOVES knuckle bones.  Mya is now solid and chunky and has most of her hair.  She is so funny and goofy and playful and affectionate.  WITH PEOPLE.  However, because she does NOT like other animals, she must be an only pet in an all adult home.  She has great indoor manners.  Likes to play fetch.  Not a huge fan of walking.  Likes to snuggle and wrestle. If you are the person who can give Mya the love and forever home she SO DESERVES, please contact Bev at 804-248-3042 or trampsrescue@yahoo.com.

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name's Ember!  I was recently brought to the shelter and am looking for a great new family to become a part of.  Unfortunately my last home wasn't the best one.  When I came to the shelter I was missing some of my fur, had a skin infection, and I was scared.  I'm all better now though and I'm ready for my new family!

I would prefer a home where I can be the only pet.  I'm up to date on vaccinations, spayed, and I also have a microchip! I love to go for walks and I like to play too.  Sometimes it takes a little time for me to warm up and trust new people, but once I do I'm a very friendly girl!!

If you're looking for a new furry family member and think I might be the pup for you please stop by the shelter and spend some time getting to know me!

animal.description:
Nice to meet you, my name is Riggs. I am a 1 and a half year old Rottweiler mix that found my way to Foothills Humane Society after being found hanging out at a local gas station. I am as sweet as sugar and a true gentleman. Sit, lie down, and shake are just some of the things I know and learn I new things quickly. I am very gentle and calm and would be the perfect addition to a family. I have been spending time in foster care where I love spending time with my pawrents and going on adventures. Here's a tidbit from a report card that my foster parents gave me: 

"Riggs is such a doll! He is a lover boy. He is usually sitting in between us on the couch or nearby on the chair. He is very calm and relaxed and enjoys lots of naps and down time. He loves to play tug of war and go for walks but doesn't seem to be a super high energy dog. He's perfect in this sense - he loves walks and small hikes and will play but is also happy to relax and be where you are. It's perfect! He does great on the leash. Hardly pulls and listens very well. He doesn't love his crate, but once we get him in it with a treat, he's fine and doesn't make a peep. We have left him in our bedroom while we've been out and I came back to him relaxing on the bed. He didn't potty or chew anything and was perfectly fine. Very impressive! He hasn't had an accident in the house once! He seems to be perfectly potty trained but we are still trying to learn his cues for when he wants to go outside. He likes other people and is happy to see them with a wagging tail. He has the cutest underbite and is so good! We love him and wants to find him a wonderful home!! He truly deserves it and will make someone so happy!"

I am heartworm positive, but that doesn't mean my heart has any less love to give. The humans tell me not to worry because heartworms are very common in strays like me, but the good news is that I am easily curable! Foothills Humane Society will even cover the expenses of my heartworm treatment until I am negative. For more information on heartworms, read this awesome article by The American Heartworm Society: https://www.heartwormsociety.org/heartworms-in-dogs

If you are interested in giving me a home, please fill out an adoption application online through our website, foothillshumanesociety.org.

animal.description:
TESS    SHEPHERD DOG/MAREMMA SHEEP DOG MIX    BLONDE    FEMALE TWO-YEARS-OLD    66LBS    CHIPPED     "LOCO" BUT IN  A GOOD WAY =) 

***Petfinder inquiries will not be answered. Please follow visit our website for more information on how to meet adoptable pets and how to submit an adoption application***

We are available to show adoptable pets, to approved applicants and by appointment only. Available appointment times fill up quickly so please visit our website and follow the instructions regarding visits and adoption practices.
 
INTERESTED IN MEETING AND/OR ADOPTING OUR ADOPTABLE PETS? 

TO ENSURE THE SAFTEY OF OUR COMMUNITY AND STAFF AND TO UTILIZE OUR LIMITED TIME TO INTRODUCE FOLKS TO ADOPTABLE PETS AS EFFICIENTLY  AS POSSIBLE WE ARE ONLY SCHEUDLING APPOINTMENTS TO MEET ADOPTABLE PETS WITH PRE-APPROVED APPLICANTS. TO PRACTICE SOCIAL DISTANCING EFFECTIVELY WE ARE ASKING THAT ALL INTERESTED PARTIES MAKE AN APPOINTMENT TO MEET OUR ADOPTBALE PETS. 

HAVING A PRE-APPROVED APPLICATION DOESN'T OBLIGATE YOU TO ADOPT FROM US AND IS FREE! PLEASE VISIT OUR WEBSITE AT WWW.ELMORESPCA.ORG  TO FILL OUT AND SUBMIT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION ELECTRONICALLY.

WE ARE ASKING FOLKS TO GIVE US A 7-14 BUSINESS DAY WINDOW TO PROCESS APPLICATIONS AS WE ARE RECEIVING SO MANY! YOU WILL RECEIVE AN EMAIL TO SCHEDULE AN APPOINTMENT AS SOON AS YOUR APPLICATION IS PROCESSED. 

WE ADVOCATE FOR OUR WARDS AGGRESSIVELY UNTIL AN APPROVED APPLICANT, WHO IS A GREAT MATCH, VERBALLY COMMITS TO ADOPT THAT PET.  


Hi Tess, 
I miss you so much! I can't believe it will be, on 12/17/20, five months since you were rescued by RCAPS and sent to Elmore SPCA to meet your new family! I saw your picture the other day and it brought back fond memories of cuddling with you, of playing with you and of the time we spent together.  I will always be in awe of your ability to learn and of your capacity to love. Do you still play with any toy you can get your paws on? Are you still super excited to go for long walks, hikes and runs?   I know you love your ball and your chew toy and am so happy that you get to play with them daily at the shelter.   
I heard that when you arrived at the shelter you were a bit unsure and wild and would bark at everyone you met. We talked about that before you left and you said you were going to mellow out on that, remember??? 
 It's okay though; I know that is hard to enter a new situation and that you like to bark when you are behind a fence or barrier.  I also heard that you tested positive for ehrilichia, but that the folks at Elmore treated you for that. How are you feeling? 
I know that you have been adopted out to two households and it didn't work out  because you are a high energy dog and didn't want to share your space with other pets. I just know that you are going to find the right home soon!  I know that you like to be around people who will give you leadership and who will allow you the opportunity to burn off all that energy! All you need to do is look for a home with folks who love to go for runs, hikes or who have a big yard in which you can run and play fetch!  I would stay away from any homes with cats and other dogs to make sure that you get ALL the attention. 
Tess, you are a gorgeous and amazing dog! You are smart, fun, lively, engaging and you have a super personality. I know that you are going to find your new beginning soon. Keep your muzzle up and make sure you sit for treats!
All of us have our paws crossed for you...
Love, 
Your pals at Vance County Services in North Carolina

animal.description:
Sawyer and Cooper came to us when a State Police officer got a call about 2 dogs being abandoned. These two boys were starving and had so many collars and tie outs on them it was horrifying. 

They both are super sweet and have amazing personalities. They are both so grateful the officer fed them and brought them to us. They were both so scared .
These two have been together their whole life. They are bonded and we can't imagine separating them. They will cry if one is not with the other. They need each other. 

Sawyer and Cooper are not rowdy, they are not fearful, they are huge lovers. They just want to be wanted together and live their best life off a chain, with someone who will treat them as they deserve to be treated, which is , with love and compassion. They have great personalities and are super sweet. We understand they are a lot of dog, but they truly are inseparable.

*Sawyer and Cooper MUST be adopted together

animal.description:
Please contact Sandi (outlaw7148@yahoo.com) for more information about this pet.Bonded PairWe show our dogs by appointment only upon receipt of an online application which can be found at kcpaws.petfinder.com If you are reading this we are still accepting applications for these pets. The adoption fee for Mijo & Erasmo will be $250
BONDED PAIR
Meet Mijo and Erasmo!! These sweet senior boys are 9 years old and are litter mates that have been together their whole lives. We would like to find them a loving home with room for both of them. These older boys still have plenty of energy and TONS of love to give. Like most chihuahuas, they like to attach to one person. Once you become that person... prepare to be showered in love and adoration! They will follow you like a shadow! Mijo loves to play with stuffed animals and wearing soft sweaters! Erasmo is the more confident brother who is always leading the way and looking out for his brother. They recently had dentals and each had to have teeth removed, they've only got a few teeth between the two of them but hey, it adds character! They are kennel trained and are great about keeping their area clean, we believe once they get a routine and know where to go they will housetrain quickly. They are not very fond of small children so a home with no kids under teenage years would be best. they get along fine with other dogs, but also like typical chihuahua's they don't like to share their space or their human with 'outsiders' so they can be a bit sassy. Mijo unfortunately has a heart mummer, and has had a few small seizures that we know of. But he seems happy and gets around just fine. But he may need more frequent vet visits to check on his heart health as he ages. If you have room in your heart for this special pair please fill out our online adoption application.

animal.description:
Our adoption process:
Step 1: Please fill out an application.
Step 2: Interview with adoption counselor.
Step 3: If you're the right match, you may be able to meet the animal today, or set up an appointment to meet the animal when we have more time available to ensure it's the right match.
Step 4: Depending on your home and readiness, you may be able to take an animal home today.
*Please note that due to a high volume of interest in some of our animals, we may take multiple applications to ensure everyone gets a chance to apply and be interviewed. We don't do our adoptions on first come first serve basis, we instead focus on matchmaking to ensure the perfect match for both the animal and adopter.

DOB: 4/28/2019
Breed: Whippet/Terrier Mix
Neutered Male
Adoption Fee: $350

A little bit about me...
I am a happy dog who's having so much fun meeting all kinds of new friends here at the shelter! I am very friendly, and I want to say hello to every dog and person I meet while out on a walk. My over friendliness can be off-putting to some dogs, and I don't get the hint when another dog doesn't want to play with me. It'll be up to my humans to keep an eye on this to keep me safe. I have a lot of energy and can outlast most of the puppies in a playgroup, so please be ready to provide me a lot of exercise.

The highlights...

I am very bouncy and happy
I will bark when I have pent up energy
I am a social butterfly
Needs an active home so I don't get bored
I need to be provided with outlets for my energy
I love playing with friendly dogs

My ideal home would include...

A family that has time, patience, and a plan for potty training. Any dog that's introduced to a new environment is bound to have accidents, whether they're an adult dog or a puppy. I will need my humans to have a plan for potty training and show me where and when I'm expected to go potty.

I am very young and hyperactive, so I am looking for a home that will exercise me daily, so I don't get bored and develop destructive behaviors. These long legs can walk for miles and miles so don't worry about me getting tired on a hike! I have the stamina and energy to be able to keep up.

I am young and have a lot of energy so daily walks are a must for me! I would be a great candidate for a dog park, or to accompany you when visiting with friends and family that have dogs in their home. Keeping me well socialized will help me become a well rounded and confident adult dog.

animal.description:
If you are interested in any of the dogs available at New Leash Rescue, you can reach out to the foster listed below for more information and then complete an adoption application which can be found at https://www.newleashrescue.org/adopt/policy.  Please email the completed application to newleashrescue2018@gmail.com

Holly is a one and a half year old who loves to snuggle with her people and her fur-siblings. She is said to be a Pitbull/ Boxer mix, so needs a family that can keep her busy. She gets along well with everyone and enjoys being around her people. She is potty and crate trained, but may have accidents when transitioning to a new home. She can whine in her crate and bark at noises she is unsure of, so no shared walls or this girl. 

When encountering new things, Holly can be reserved and may sometimes bark at people (especially in her home), but will stop when told firmly. Holly does become timid when shouting happens and may pancake to the floor. She will need a family who is willing to take the time to bring her everywhere dogs are allowed so she can realize that no one will do anything to hurt her, she’s a very fast learner. 

Holly has never been an only dog, so another dog in the home is preferable as she does take cues from her foster siblings on how to act. Holly currently lives with four other dogs and does great! She loves to snuggle with her foster fur-siblings, even when they would rather not. She is in a foster home with cats and does okay with them as long as they don’t run, or she will chase. Holly does redirect quickly and will stop mid-run if you tell her no. Homes without cats would be preferable as she would have the most success in a non-temptation filled environment. 

In her previous home, Holly would get loose off of a tie out and would not stay in the area - she would run.  Holly will require a fenced in yard for her safety.  

Holly is one of the sweetest pups and will snuggle with you for hours and hours, after a good amount of exercise. Are you willing to let Holly snuggle her way into your heart? If so, please fill out an application on New Leash Rescue website.

Adoption fee is $350.00 + tax (no checks) 

Foster to contact: Annie @ fosterannie2017@gmail.com

Holly will be at our adoption event on Saturday from 11-2pm at the Woodbury PetSmart.  

Our fosters do the best they can to provide all information about the animal's background and temperament while in foster care in their home. An adopters routine and home environment is likely going to be different than that in their foster home. 

Sometimes there is more that comes out about a dog's personality once they have been able to settle in a home and truly become comfortable. There are great articles out there written about the different stages a pet goes through after adoption, discussing transitions that happen at 3 days, 3 weeks, and 3 months. We highly recommend reading about this - it will help you understand the transition your new pet goes through.

animal.description:
Blue is an approximately 2 year old aussie (no tail), and is a transfer from a shelter partner where he was found stray. Thus far, while he can be forward on initial meeting, he is good with other dogs, humans, and has met a cat without incident. We do not have history with Blue and children, and will not place him into a home where young children reside.
.
Blue will do best in a very active, training centric home with other active, playful dogs already in residence. Fenced yard is preferable due to his drive.
.
Blue currently weighs 48lbs and is quite fit. He is located in Maryland, we do not ship dogs, and will not be adopting Blue outside of the mid Atlantic region.


PLEASE READ our procedures for adoption prior to making inquiry regarding this dog. If you are looking for additional photos, video, or information on this dog, you will likely find that by searching our facebook page for their photo/description album.
.
Please see our main website at www.mabcr.org for more information regarding the adoption of this or any dog from our rescue. 
.
Please note that while this dog is currently available, any dog on our site may have an adoption pending and may not be available to you at this time. The same dog may later become available if the adoption falls through. 
.
Our website www.mabcr.org will give you details on our adoption procedures as well as an application for adoption. An application must be submitted prior to 'matching' an adopter with a dog as all dogs do not fit into all homes. We pride ourselves in our adoption process, we take the time to get to know our adopters so that we can place a dog with them that they can enjoy for years to come.
.
Please understand that we will not discuss dogs with individual adopters until after the application process is completed.
.
Our rescue does not have a public facility, therefore there are no visiting hours. Appointments to visit with the available dogs are made after the application process has been completed by our staff.  
.
To assist any dog within the MABCR organization, please consider making a donation to the general fund or to the medical fund. All dogs coming into our rescue are fully vetted (s/n and core vaccines) prior to adoption.
.
Rescuing animals is quite expensive. If you are unable to adopt, but would like to help this, or any other animal in our system, please consider a sponsorship donation. 
For information on our sponsorship program, please contact Sarah at SLR@mabcr.org. 
.
Thank you for your interest in Mid-Atlantic Border Collie Rescue.

animal.description:
Isn't this the most handsome fellow in the world? Cash is a vibrant one year old male Dane/GSD mix (75 lbs.). While we are unsure of his past, he has shown his foster family that he adores his humans. Cash recovered from serious injuries sustained from being hit by a car.  His broken tibia and dislocated hip were repaired by wonderful  ortho surgeon. He received outstanding care from his vet and tender kisses and rehab from his amazing foster.  

Cash is house and kennel trained, loves sticks (of all sizes) and chewing his peanut butter filled Kongs. MOST OF ALL, he loves a soft blanket to suck on (OMG, like a puppy). He will lay (or roll around) on his blanket and never destroys it.  Cash is still considered a pup and will require an adopter with large dog experienced, committed to enrolling him in obedience training. Because of his size, he will be placed in a home with no small children or cats. Cash is currently with a trainer who is getting him ready for his forever home (leash training, basic commands, manners, etc.).   Cash will need a home and will not be suitable for life in an apartment.  HIs adopter will need to continue his training.

We expect Cash to join us in Maine the end of January.



Adoption fees cover age specific vaccinations, spay/neuter, microchip, heartworm/lyme/ehrlichia test, worming and transport fees. 

Adoption fees: 
Through 6 months of age $450; 
7 months to through 5 years $400; 
6 years and under 9 years $325: bonded pairs are $500; 
9 years and older $250: bonded pairs are $300 

This dog is available unless it is marked as Pending, meaning Pending Adoption. This dog is in foster care locally, ONLY if Maine or New Hampshire is listed next to the dogs name; otherwise, the dog is still waiting with our partner rescue for an adoption or foster home in New England. 

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior dogs have a history of being kept up to date on rabies and distemper, have had annual heartworm tests, and are on heartworm preventative at least 6 months of the year. Current pets must by spayed/neutered. 

Imported dogs are transported on a USDA approved transport with a Health Certificate. All imported dogs are quarantined 14 days prior to getting on transport.

animal.description:
How do you do,

My name is Devon.  Did you know that my name is a pretty and popular British-place name?  It evokes the beautiful country of farmlands and dramatic seascapes and moors in southwest England.

Apparently my original owner did not feel that I was beautiful enough to keep anymore, since once I had my last litter of pups they abandoned me.  Sometimes people are so heartless.

Any who, a very nice land owner found me.  I was significantly malnourished.  They contacted the local sheriff's office, who in turn contacted Lucies project.  The landowner had attempted to catch me so I could be taken somewhere and treated, however I was very afraid and kept running away.  2 very nice ladies from Lucies finally coaxed me over to them while the landowner and sheriff's deputy looked for my pups.  They were no where to be found. :(

I was taken to the vet to be checked out.  I was so underweight that I could not even be spayed.  I had to wait a number of weeks before that could happen!  My body condition was so poor, that the ladies were unsure of when I had even delivered my last litter of pups. I'm only 3 years old and have probably had more litters of pups than I should have in my short life.  I was a sad sight for sure.

Now though, I have a clean bill of health.  I'm telling you, these peeps here at the rescue took good care of me.  So patient and kind and caring, I love them all!

 I like to run and play, but most of all I like affection and crave human attention.

Are you like me as well, and just need someone to cuddle with?  Come meet me, I'm sure we will both fall in love at first site!

*** We strive to ensure our dogs are going to a safe, loving and caring home. Phone interviews are required for all adoptions****

animal.description:
Bambi - mixed breed, 30 lbs. Good with dogs. No cats. Kids over 12.

Meet Bambi! Rescued from life on the streets, together with her sister Star, we are in love with this adorable girl.

Bambi is medium in size, with timid but kind personality. She is a sweet and very affectionate girl who needs just a little bit more confidence. She likes walks but can be easily intimidated when out on the street. A more quiet residential area will be best for her. Busy city streets are not her thing. She needs a home with a yard.

From her foster:

Bambi is a very sweet and loving girl she will roll over onto her back to ask for belly rubs. She is a true couch potato, Bami loves to burrow into a blanket and snuggle on the couch with you. She is a little shy when it comes to meeting new dogs or people. Bambi knows how to sit and is potty trained as well as very food motivated. She also enjoys a good chew to work on such as a bone, kong, pig ear, snuffle mat, etc. Needs to have a high fence in the yard, as she can jump high.

She will do best in a home with another dog to give her some confidence. Bambi has a little separation anxiety and does not love being alone. This needs some work.

She is vaccinated, spayed and chipped. Her adoption fee is $395.

We cover the medical to prepare the pet for adoption and the adopt donations go directly to cover those costs and range from $295-$495. Thank you for stepping up to save a life!

To expedite to meet with this dog, please go to our site at www.savinggreatanimals.org and fill out an application. We look at the first applications to arrive, so we hope to hear from you soon!

animal.description:
Come in and meet our newest addition, Luna.  She is a very pretty, young boxer mix who was found as a stray and brought in to C.A.R.E.  She is about 18 months old and weighs close to 50 pounds. She has been vaccinated, spayed, and is heartworm negative.

We have found that Luna is very smart!  While she has not had the benefit of training, she learns quickly and her negative behaviors can be redirected. 

Luna is a real people lover and eagerly greets our volunteers with happy tail wags.  She is very active and wants to run and play all day! She will also try to dig her way out of her kennel, if left alone too long, so her adopters will have to have a fenced yard.

Due to her high activity level, lack of restraint and her strength, we will not be able to adopt her out to any families with children under 13. 

Luna will have to be an only pet because she does not like any other animals. She is very reactive to all the other dogs in the shelter.

They have been treated for Heartworm, and are vaccinated and neutered, of course. 
 The third brother, Spot, was fostered and then adopted.  These two are super bonded.  They play, they share, they are best friends.  They are REALLY REALLY HIGH ENERGY, but sweet.  Flop is not only a name, it is a description, and action.  He does it A LOT.  Dot is more shy, but has come a long way since here at the rescue.  Really wanting to adopt these as a pair.  They like to go on walks.  They do not jump a 5 foot fence.  They can dig, but not to escape. Despite these multiple changes in homes and people, Jenny is a very Zen puppy. Polite in waiting her turn to go outside and playful with other dogs she meets as well. She has a passion for running, so anyone who runs would find her the perfect companion for that exercise. She's great with kids ages ten and over (too exuberant for younger kids) and has also been fine around cats! We're told she could use "a little leash work, but she's just a puppy, so that should be expected. Jenny will make a wonderful addition to any active household with a fenced back yard and a playmate.

animal.description:
Mybella is an extremely fun, happy, goofy and energetic adolescent pup, who is looking for a warm and comfy home to flop down in. Because she lived outside her whole life, she has very little understanding of indoor dog boundaries. For example, she likes to oversee any kind of cooking endeavour and afterwards, she likes to be certain the countertops are properly tidy and clear of leftovers. This is something she will need more work on to understand she isn't suited for such an important supervisory role. She is doing much better with potty training and frequently escorts herself to the back door to use the outhouse, but she will need continued reinforcement in a new environment. She loves toys! Either food or toys will work for training purposes. She thrives with positive reinforcement training methods.

She loves to play with other dogs of all sizes and would likely do best with another prosocial active dog as a companion and playmate. Mybella's ideal home would also consist of training partners who will, with love, patience and dedication, work with her to help her on her journey in becoming the best dog she can be. If you are interested in Mybella, please contact Angels today!

For inquiries, email inquiry@angelsrescue.org

An Adoption Application for this dog can be found and submitted online. http://www.angelsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-forms

Please be sure to like our Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/angelsrescue.

animal.description:
Little Miss Ruby, all 16lbs of her, is 80% adorable and 20% sassy.  She is housetrained, crate trained and listens to commands pretty well. Walks nice on a leash but, reacts to bicycles, joggers and some vehicles.  She LOVES her toys so much that she can be possessive of them. These behaviors are manageable and overtime can be corrected. Ruby gets excited & jumpy during play time so it is recommended that she not be in a home with children. 

She is extremely affectionate & really enjoys cuddling either right next to you or on top of you.  She adores her one on one time so much that a home without lots of visitors would be to her delight.

She lives with a large young male and a medium size older female dog but shows no interest in playing with them...she prefers a dog her own size.  Ruby would also be fine as an only dog because she is all about her toys and/or an outdoor game of toss. This medium energy cutie would do well in a home with a fenced in yard.  The noisy active apartment life does not appeal to her.  Her family should be experienced dog owners that have time to play with her, walk her and give her lots of love. And, in return, she will give you lots of love and laughs.

animal.description:
Meet Snickers!!

Snickers is a border terrier mix at the young age of 6yrs and 11months.
Snickers is breaking our hearts. He has lost EVERYTHING, his beloved owner who passed away, he lost his home and even siblings birdie and fishy. The toys he came with and there were many (which shows how adored he was from his owner) are literally all he has from his previous life.

He is good with other dogs and cats but we would recommend he be an only dog with no children as he is being possessive over his toys. This is very likely because that is all he has to hold onto from his previous life and he is used to being a spoiled only pup. With no toys on the scene he is cool, so can easily be walked with other dogs.

He has been an only dog his whole life and very well cared for so we are not surprised he is really struggling, he is grieving, his whole world for the last 7years has just disappeared.
He will make a wonderful dog for someone who can show him his life can be great again with another family. As we said he loves toys and is a master at playing fetch!!

Do you have it in your heart to help out this gorgeous boy? 1/11/21 10:21 PM

animal.description:
Hi friends my name is Cow and I'm a 13-year-old Great Dane / Lab mix. I definitely have Great Dane features but I'm not too big at just under 60 pounds. I'm a goofy boy who is still pretty active in my mature years. I enjoy playing with my human friends and can go on those long walks with you... I'll even keep up with you like those young bucks! I do not enjoy the company of other dogs however, so you will just have to give me all your love... *wink wink*!  Even though I'm not as big as a normal Great Dane, I would appreciate not having any kids too young or small, after all I am an older guy that needs a calmer and respectful energy when it comes to those little humans. I do have a bit of separation anxiety and would prefer a home where my human is with me the majority of the time. 

If you are interested in meeting me, please email adoption@sdsanctuary.com and set up an appointment!

animal.description:
Foxy is an adorable 1 yr old, 28 lb Shepherd mix with a beautiful soft coat.  She is a bit shy at first but does love people and will bond quickly. She seems to be good with other dogs but a proper meet and greet is required. As you can see in her photos she did have a best dog buddy in her last foster home. Foxy is an energetic girl so an active family will be best for her.  She requires a home with children over 12 years of age.  And, we do not know how she is with cats.  A secure fenced yard is required. No apartments/condos for this girl. 





Our adoption fee of $250.00 helps cover expenses (vaccinations, microchips, spay/neuter, food, housing) for the homeless pets we rescue.  UAF does NOT ship or adopt our adoptables out of state (Arizona) and to ensure the best fit, UAF conducts a home visit to meet other pets and verify a safe, secure yard.

To start the process of adopting this dog or any other dog, please fill out our matchmaking form which can be accessed by copying the following address and pasting it into your browser.  Filling out this form does not obligate you to adopt.

https://www.unitedanimalfriends.org/form/2-dog-matchmaking-form

Please email uafdogs20@gmail.com to learn more about this dog.

*** Adoption Pending***

LEO is a younger malamute filled with energy and joy for life, ready to roll right over for tummy rubs! In fact, our WAMAL volunteer described him as 'all over the place, so happy, goofy, playful.' He can start off a little shy, but opens up and is very friendly with people and does well with dogs of his energy level and general size. In fact, he would love to have another dog pal! He enjoys playing with other dogs and getting out his boundless energy. Leo knows some basic commands including 'come', 'sit', 'leave it', and 'stay' (when he is not too excited!) and will enjoy learning more in his new home. He needs to work on his leash skills. He is house trained and happily sleeps in his crate at night. His foster home reports he 'seems to want to pretty much always be with us and the dogs as a group.' As expected with his breed, Leo does not do well with small critters so needs to kept away from cats and chickens. To be fair about the chickens - they do taste delicious! Leo would do best in an active home with adults and possibly older children where he can bond with his new pack over some outdoor adventures and indoor snuggle time!Interested in sponsoring? See our sponsorship information.

animal.description:
Apply to adopt Daphne here https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/KGDR/Dog

Daphne is  about 6 years old and weighs 105 lbs. The vet has given her a clean bill of health, and says she looks and acts great. She is energetic and loves attention.  She is very well behaved and quite loving. She is quiet and only barks to alert us. She loves kids and adults, once they are introduced and sniffed. She is great with cats.

We have attempted a few times to introduce Daphne to other dogs, but she seems to be afraid as well as protective for the family and the kids. The Pandemic has limited  our attempts for dog socialization training.  We feel she needs more interaction to help her to become comfortable with other dogs. Other than that, she is house, crate and electric fence trained. She does very well in the crate for extended periods, such as overnight or when we go to work. (We plan to send her crate with her to help her in the adjustment). 

She is learning to walk with a harness and leash. She still pulls a bit, but is controllable for most of her walk with simple commands and reassurance. She is eager to go in the car and rides well.  She has learned several helpful commands and allows us to bathe her, check her mouth/teeth, takes oral medications easily with peanut butter, and does not bother or eat anything left on the kitchen counter. She does not get on furniture. She loves to play with adults and kids.  Lives to fetch balls and play with her toys. She likes to run and show off in the yard. Daphne is searching for a loving home with playful kids and hopefully a big yard to run and play. She may do best in a single dog setting. Daph is such a loving dog and would be a blessing to a family that will love her as much as we do. She's a real sweetie!

PS. She is a master at getting love and affection while leaning against you and burying her head. We call her "The Queen of Lean"! Z Daphne is spayed and up to date on vaccinations.

animal.description:
Hickory was turned over to our shelter partner as a border collie/aussie mix. At 70lbs, and in good shape, it seems that perhaps something else is in the mix as well. Regardless, Hickory is a delightfully sweet young (@2 years) guy who just wants to be with his people and do fun stuff.
.
Hickory LOVES playing with other dogs (see video in comments) and has been great with every dog he has met. Here, he has ignored the chickens and cats, though no promises in his new home -- I'm with him, and call him off before he has a chance to be dumb.
.
Hickory will do best in an active home that enjoys games, hiking, and long walks, and while we think he would be ok as an only dog, he'd love to have another playful dog in his home.
.
Hickory is well crate trained, and appears to have been previously housebroken. He located in Maryland. We do not ship dogs, and will not be adopting him outside of the mid Atlantic region.
.


PLEASE READ our procedures for adoption prior to making inquiry regarding this dog. If you are looking for additional photos, video, or information on this dog, you will likely find that by searching our facebook page for their photo/description album.
.
Please see our main website at www.mabcr.org for more information regarding the adoption of this or any dog from our rescue. 
.
Please note that while this dog is currently available, any dog on our site may have an adoption pending and may not be available to you at this time. The same dog may later become available if the adoption falls through. 
.
Our website www.mabcr.org will give you details on our adoption procedures as well as an application for adoption. An application must be submitted prior to 'matching' an adopter with a dog as all dogs do not fit into all homes. We pride ourselves in our adoption process, we take the time to get to know our adopters so that we can place a dog with them that they can enjoy for years to come.
.
Please understand that we will not discuss dogs with individual adopters until after the application process is completed.
.
Our rescue does not have a public facility, therefore there are no visiting hours. Appointments to visit with the available dogs are made after the application process has been completed by our staff.  
.
To assist any dog within the MABCR organization, please consider making a donation to the general fund or to the medical fund. All dogs coming into our rescue are fully vetted (s/n and core vaccines) prior to adoption.
.
Rescuing animals is quite expensive. If you are unable to adopt, but would like to help this, or any other animal in our system, please consider a sponsorship donation. 
For information on our sponsorship program, please contact Sarah at SLR@mabcr.org. 
.
Thank you for your interest in Mid-Atlantic Border Collie Rescue.

animal.description:
WE ARE SORRY BUT WE ONLY ADOPT WITHIN THE STATE OF FLORIDA

Balto is a previous SHRF Husky who, unfortunately, has made his way back to us. The family situation and environment has changed and Balto did not adjust well to the situation. It broke their hearts to let him go but his previous owners want what is best for him. 

Based his energy level you would never guess that Balto is 10 years old; he is still quite active. He is very affectionate and eager to please, although he is a head strong Husky. Like most senior dogs, Balto prefers consistency through a routine. 

He gets along well with other dogs. loves his walks and does well on lead as long as there is not a squirrel or stray cat in sight. He is quite happy to go for car rides and will rotate from watching out the window to laying down to trying to get as close to you as possible. Like most dogs, he enjoys receiving belly rubs. 

Balto is healthy, Heartworm negative, current on vaccines, neutered, and microchipped. He needs a new loving home to live out his remaining years. Give him that chance and fill out an adoption application on our website, www.siberrescue.com, today.

animal.description:
Pomoppossum is officially ready for adoption!!!!  For those who don't know, Pomoppossum is urinary and fecal incontinent due to hemivertebrae.  He has no tail because of this, as well.  But of all the incontinent dogs we've ever had... he was the easiest....and his foster mom this go around (who also has plenty of incontinent experience) agrees.  He is easy to manage a belly band on and well, you all know the story of his poops...he just shoots a tiny hard little poop ball randomly which might sound strange, but in our world, it just sounds easy!!!!  
We are so excited for him to find his perfect home!!! We wanted to wait since it had been 2.5 years since his previous adoption, to see who this boy has grown up to be, and here is what we know..... 
He is not the wild child he once was, but he will need a fenced in yard, wood preferred!  He still loves to play, enjoys his toys, and absolutely need a canine playmate, he loves to play!  He is fun but also laid back.  He is a great snuggler with his human as well.  For all his character and wit, he has grown into a well behaved little man!!!


Pomopposum is up to date on shots and preventatives and is microchipped.    His adoption fee is any donation you feel appropriate.  Our adoption fee is set to a level to make adoptions happen.  They do not cover our costs. Thank you for your generosity and interest in our dogs!   

All dogs adopted locally through SGDR receive a free six-week session of obedience classes and a lifetime of behavior support through our Project REWARD program with trainer Charlotte Blake.

You must have an approved application before being able to visit a dog. Visit our website below for an adoption application https://www.snootygiggles.com/dog-application/

If you expect to leave the dog alone for long periods of time, please do not consider adopting a puppy.  Puppies need lots of attention and companionship.  Thanks.

All known information about the animal is listed above. We do our best to give accurate information, but most of our dogs are rescues and do not come with a known history.

animal.description:
Meet Tootsie! At 2.5 years old and 35 lbs, she's a short, but stocky lovebug with a fabulous underbite. Tootsie is a great combo of active and couch potato. She loves having a big yard to run around and play fetch, but is also happy to chill on the sofa in a quiet home. Tootsie is good with other dogs but does like to play at full speed, so she'll do best with dogs her own size or bigger. This sweet girl is also very smart and likes to gather up toys to show off to her humans. But when her humans have to go to work, Tootsie is perfectly happy to stay in her crate and entertain herself with a chew bone. When you get home, Tootsie will jump in your lap for hugs and kisses. Fill out an adoption or foster application to meet this adorable, easygoing pup! 

-----
IMPORTANT: To protect the health of our staff and volunteers, ARF is currently conducting adoptions by appointment only. Please see more information below.

-Contact Info:
Have questions first about the adoption process or a particular animal? Please click the Contact this Organization button.

-Ready to Adopt? Please visit www.animalrescuemobile.org to submit an adoption application, or click the Adopt Me button to request one via email.

-The Adoption Process:
An adoption application, veterinarian and/or personal reference, a home visit, and a $150 adoption fee are part of the process. All animals will be up to date on shots, microchipped, and spayed/neutered before adoption.

-Please Note:
Sponsors are needed to help ARF with the cost of vet care. If you would like to sponsor an ARF rescue, please click the Sponsor Me button. A sponsor donation of $50 will help cover the cost of a spay/neuter surgery. Plus, ARF is a non-profit organization and all donations are tax deductible.

TILLY IS LOOKING FOR HER FOREVER FAMILY! Tilly is approximately 4 years old and came to The Arrow Fund after suffering a complete degloving of the right back foot. After months of trying to save her leg, the veterinary team decided amputation was the only way to ensure she had a normal, pain free life.  Her foster said that being a tripod weighing 52 lbs. has not slowed her down. She has a bright personality and loves short walks but gets tired after about a half a mile. She enjoys a good game of tug of war and loves playing with tennis balls. She also is good at making her presence known and will bark at just about anything. She is good with cats, dogs and children over 12. If you are ready to have this ray of light join your family, adoption applications are on our website.

animal.description:
Meet this beautiful girl named Carmen!! She came into the shelter November 23, 2020 as a stray and was never reclaimed so she’s now awaiting her adoption day! She came in a little unsure and has gotten more comfortable and we have learned she needs a owner that has time and patience to work with her. She’s needs training and needs to learn some manners. She likes to jump up on you and bite at the rope leash (so we are using a chain leash while walking). She can be nippy with people I think thinking she’s playing but we are working with her on that. She is beautiful and full of love to share just don’t think whoever had her spent much time with her. She has potential just need consistency and training. She is around 2 years old, current on shots, and deserving a wonderful home that can give her training and TLC she deserves and needs. Maybe you have the most amazing FOREVER home for Carmen?! Visit with her today!
If you have another dog and are interested in meeting another potential new furry member please bring him or her to the shelter and meet on neutral ground before adopting. No need to shuffle the animals around any more than necessary. Please know that 1 mosquito bite can create heart worms and they can be fatal if not treated. It is VERY important to keep your pets healthy and protected by keeping them on a once a month heart worm and flea/tick prevention. These animals are counting on you as their owner to provide them with lots a love and the proper health care so PLEASE make sure you are aware and prepared before adopting. Owning a pet is an extra expense and responsibility but is so worth every minute and penny you invest in them. They will add lots of joy and unconditional love if given a fair chance.
The shelter is open Mon.-Fri. 10-1, 2-5 and Sat. 10-4. Adopt a homeless pet and save a life. If you can not adopt right now come out and volunteer and make a difference in the lives of these animals while they await their FOREVER home.
animal.name: Carmen
